58 throughout the translation unit. */
59 int initializations_p;
60 /* Nonzero if there have been any destructions at this priority
61 throughout the translation unit. */
62 int destructions_p;
63} *priority_info;

112/* Return a member function type (a METHOD_TYPE), given FNTYPE (a
113 FUNCTION_TYPE), CTYPE (class type), and QUALS (the cv-qualifiers
114 that apply to the function). */
115
116tree
117build_memfn_type (tree fntype, tree ctype, cp_cv_quals quals,
118 cp_ref_qualifier rqual)
119{
120 tree raises;
121 tree attrs;
122 int type_quals;
123 bool late_return_type_p;
124
125 if (fntype == error_mark_node || ctype == error_mark_node)
126 return error_mark_node;
127
128 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (fntype) == FUNCTION_TYPE
129 || TREE_CODE (fntype) == METHOD_TYPE);
130
131 type_quals = quals & ~TYPE_QUAL_RESTRICT;
132 ctype = cp_build_qualified_type (ctype, type_quals);
133 raises = TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (fntype);
134 attrs = TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (fntype);
135 late_return_type_p = TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE (fntype);
136 fntype = build_method_type_directly (ctype, TREE_TYPE (fntype),
137 (TREE_CODE (fntype) == METHOD_TYPE
138 ? TREE_CHAIN (TYPE_ARG_TYPES (fntype))
139 : TYPE_ARG_TYPES (fntype)));
140 if (attrs)
141 fntype = cp_build_type_attribute_variant (fntype, attrs);
142 if (rqual)
143 fntype = build_ref_qualified_type (fntype, rqual);
144 if (raises)
145 fntype = build_exception_variant (fntype, raises);
146 if (late_return_type_p)
147 TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE (fntype) = 1;
148
149 return fntype;
150}
151
152/* Return a variant of FNTYPE, a FUNCTION_TYPE or METHOD_TYPE, with its
153 return type changed to NEW_RET. */
154
155tree
156change_return_type (tree new_ret, tree fntype)
157{
158 tree newtype;
159 tree args = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (fntype);
160 tree raises = TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (fntype);
161 tree attrs = TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (fntype);
162 bool late_return_type_p = TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE (fntype);
163
164 if (new_ret == error_mark_node)
165 return fntype;
166
167 if (same_type_p (new_ret, TREE_TYPE (fntype)))
168 return fntype;
169
170 if (TREE_CODE (fntype) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
171 {
172 newtype = build_function_type (new_ret, args);
173 newtype = apply_memfn_quals (newtype,
174 type_memfn_quals (fntype),
175 type_memfn_rqual (fntype));
176 }
177 else
178 newtype = build_method_type_directly
179 (class_of_this_parm (fntype), new_ret, TREE_CHAIN (args));
180 if (FUNCTION_REF_QUALIFIED (fntype))
181 newtype = build_ref_qualified_type (newtype, type_memfn_rqual (fntype));
182 if (raises)
183 newtype = build_exception_variant (newtype, raises);
184 if (attrs)
185 newtype = cp_build_type_attribute_variant (newtype, attrs);
186 if (late_return_type_p)
187 TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE (newtype) = 1;
188
189 return newtype;
190}

192/* Build a PARM_DECL with NAME and TYPE, and set DECL_ARG_TYPE
193 appropriately. */
194
195tree
196cp_build_parm_decl (tree name, tree type)
197{
198 tree parm = build_decl (input_location,
199 PARM_DECL, name, type);
200 /* DECL_ARG_TYPE is only used by the back end and the back end never
201 sees templates. */
202 if (!processing_template_decl)
203 DECL_ARG_TYPE (parm) = type_passed_as (type);
204
205 return parm;
206}

208/* Returns a PARM_DECL for a parameter of the indicated TYPE, with the
209 indicated NAME. */
210
211tree
212build_artificial_parm (tree name, tree type)
213{
214 tree parm = cp_build_parm_decl (name, type);
215 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (parm) = 1;
216 /* All our artificial parms are implicitly `const'; they cannot be
217 assigned to. */
218 TREE_READONLY (parm) = 1;
219 return parm;
220}

222/* Constructors for types with virtual baseclasses need an "in-charge" flag
223 saying whether this constructor is responsible for initialization of
224 virtual baseclasses or not. All destructors also need this "in-charge"
225 flag, which additionally determines whether or not the destructor should
226 free the memory for the object.
227
228 This function adds the "in-charge" flag to member function FN if
229 appropriate. It is called from grokclassfn and tsubst.
230 FN must be either a constructor or destructor.
231
232 The in-charge flag follows the 'this' parameter, and is followed by the
233 VTT parm (if any), then the user-written parms. */
234
235void
236maybe_retrofit_in_chrg (tree fn)
237{
238 tree basetype, arg_types, parms, parm, fntype;
239
240 /* If we've already add the in-charge parameter don't do it again. */
241 if (DECL_HAS_IN_CHARGE_PARM_P (fn))
242 return;
243
244 /* When processing templates we can't know, in general, whether or
245 not we're going to have virtual baseclasses. */
246 if (processing_template_decl)
247 return;
248
249 /* We don't need an in-charge parameter for constructors that don't
250 have virtual bases. */
251 if (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (fn)
252 && !CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES (DECL_CONTEXT (fn)))
253 return;
254
255 arg_types = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (fn));
256 basetype = TREE_TYPE (TREE_VALUE (arg_types));
257 arg_types = TREE_CHAIN (arg_types);
258
259 parms = DECL_CHAIN (DECL_ARGUMENTS (fn));
260
261 /* If this is a subobject constructor or destructor, our caller will
262 pass us a pointer to our VTT. */
263 if (CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES (DECL_CONTEXT (fn)))
264 {
265 parm = build_artificial_parm (vtt_parm_identifier, vtt_parm_type);
266
267 /* First add it to DECL_ARGUMENTS between 'this' and the real args... */
268 DECL_CHAIN (parm) = parms;
269 parms = parm;
270
271 /* ...and then to TYPE_ARG_TYPES. */
272 arg_types = hash_tree_chain (vtt_parm_type, arg_types);
273
274 DECL_HAS_VTT_PARM_P (fn) = 1;
275 }
276
277 /* Then add the in-charge parm (before the VTT parm). */
278 parm = build_artificial_parm (in_charge_identifier, integer_type_node);
279 DECL_CHAIN (parm) = parms;
280 parms = parm;
281 arg_types = hash_tree_chain (integer_type_node, arg_types);
282
283 /* Insert our new parameter(s) into the list. */
284 DECL_CHAIN (DECL_ARGUMENTS (fn)) = parms;
285
286 /* And rebuild the function type. */
287 fntype = build_method_type_directly (basetype, TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (fn)),
288 arg_types);
289 if (TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (TREE_TYPE (fn)))
290 fntype = build_exception_variant (fntype,
291 TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (TREE_TYPE (fn)));
292 if (TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (TREE_TYPE (fn)))
293 fntype = (cp_build_type_attribute_variant
294 (fntype, TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (TREE_TYPE (fn))));
295 TREE_TYPE (fn) = fntype;
296
297 /* Now we've got the in-charge parameter. */
298 DECL_HAS_IN_CHARGE_PARM_P (fn) = 1;
299}
300
301/* Classes overload their constituent function names automatically.
302 When a function name is declared in a record structure,
303 its name is changed to it overloaded name. Since names for
304 constructors and destructors can conflict, we place a leading
305 '$' for destructors.
306
307 CNAME is the name of the class we are grokking for.
308
309 FUNCTION is a FUNCTION_DECL. It was created by `grokdeclarator'.
310
311 FLAGS contains bits saying what's special about today's
312 arguments. DTOR_FLAG == DESTRUCTOR.
313
314 If FUNCTION is a destructor, then we must add the `auto-delete' field
315 as a second parameter. There is some hair associated with the fact
316 that we must "declare" this variable in the manner consistent with the
317 way the rest of the arguments were declared.
318
319 QUALS are the qualifiers for the this pointer. */
320
321void
322grokclassfn (tree ctype, tree function, enum overload_flags flags)
323{
324 tree fn_name = DECL_NAME (function);
325
326 /* Even within an `extern "C"' block, members get C++ linkage. See
327 [dcl.link] for details. */
328 SET_DECL_LANGUAGE (function, lang_cplusplus);
329
330 if (fn_name == NULL_TREE)
331 {
332 error ("name missing for member function");
333 fn_name = get_identifier ("<anonymous>");
334 DECL_NAME (function) = fn_name;
335 }
336
337 DECL_CONTEXT (function) = ctype;
338
339 if (flags == DTOR_FLAG)
340 DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (function) = 1;
341
342 if (flags == DTOR_FLAG || DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (function))
343 maybe_retrofit_in_chrg (function);
344}

346/* Create an ARRAY_REF, checking for the user doing things backwards
347 along the way. DECLTYPE_P is for N3276, as in the parser. */
348
349tree
350grok_array_decl (location_t loc, tree array_expr, tree index_exp,
351 bool decltype_p)
352{
353 tree type;
354 tree expr;
355 tree orig_array_expr = array_expr;
356 tree orig_index_exp = index_exp;
357 tree overload = NULL_TREE;
358
359 if (error_operand_p (array_expr) || error_operand_p (index_exp))
360 return error_mark_node;
361
362 if (processing_template_decl)
363 {
364 if (type_dependent_expression_p (array_expr)
365 || type_dependent_expression_p (index_exp))
366 return build_min_nt_loc (loc, ARRAY_REF, array_expr, index_exp,
367 NULL_TREE, NULL_TREE);
368 array_expr = build_non_dependent_expr (array_expr);
369 index_exp = build_non_dependent_expr (index_exp);
370 }
371
372 type = TREE_TYPE (array_expr);
373 gcc_assert (type);
374 type = non_reference (type);
375
376 /* If they have an `operator[]', use that. */
377 if (MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (type) || MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (index_exp)))
378 {
379 tsubst_flags_t complain = tf_warning_or_error;
380 if (decltype_p)
381 complain |= tf_decltype;
382 expr = build_new_op (loc, ARRAY_REF, LOOKUP_NORMAL, array_expr,
383 index_exp, NULL_TREE, &overload, complain);
384 }
385 else
386 {
387 tree p1, p2, i1, i2;
388
389 /* Otherwise, create an ARRAY_REF for a pointer or array type.
390 It is a little-known fact that, if `a' is an array and `i' is
391 an int, you can write `i[a]', which means the same thing as
392 `a[i]'. */
393 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE || VECTOR_TYPE_P (type))
394 p1 = array_expr;
395 else
396 p1 = build_expr_type_conversion (WANT_POINTER, array_expr, false);
397
398 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (index_exp)) == ARRAY_TYPE)
399 p2 = index_exp;
400 else
401 p2 = build_expr_type_conversion (WANT_POINTER, index_exp, false);
402
403 i1 = build_expr_type_conversion (WANT_INT | WANT_ENUM, array_expr,
404 false);
405 i2 = build_expr_type_conversion (WANT_INT | WANT_ENUM, index_exp,
406 false);
407
408 if ((p1 && i2) && (i1 && p2))
409 error ("ambiguous conversion for array subscript");
410
411 if (p1 && i2)
412 array_expr = p1, index_exp = i2;
413 else if (i1 && p2)
414 array_expr = p2, index_exp = i1;
415 else
416 {
417 error ("invalid types %<%T[%T]%> for array subscript",
418 type, TREE_TYPE (index_exp));
419 return error_mark_node;
420 }
421
422 if (array_expr == error_mark_node || index_exp == error_mark_node)
423 error ("ambiguous conversion for array subscript");
424
425 expr = build_array_ref (input_location, array_expr, index_exp);
426 }
427 if (processing_template_decl && expr != error_mark_node)
428 {
429 if (overload != NULL_TREE)
430 return (build_min_non_dep_op_overload
431 (ARRAY_REF, expr, overload, orig_array_expr, orig_index_exp));
432
433 return build_min_non_dep (ARRAY_REF, expr, orig_array_expr, orig_index_exp,
434 NULL_TREE, NULL_TREE);
435 }
436 return expr;
437}

439/* Given the cast expression EXP, checking out its validity. Either return
440 an error_mark_node if there was an unavoidable error, return a cast to
441 void for trying to delete a pointer w/ the value 0, or return the
442 call to delete. If DOING_VEC is true, we handle things differently
443 for doing an array delete.
444 Implements ARM $5.3.4. This is called from the parser. */
445
446tree
447delete_sanity (tree exp, tree size, bool doing_vec, int use_global_delete,
448 tsubst_flags_t complain)
449{
450 tree t, type;
451
452 if (exp == error_mark_node)
453 return exp;
454
455 if (processing_template_decl)
456 {
457 t = build_min (DELETE_EXPR, void_type_node, exp, size);
458 DELETE_EXPR_USE_GLOBAL (t) = use_global_delete;
459 DELETE_EXPR_USE_VEC (t) = doing_vec;
460 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (t) = 1;
461 return t;
462 }
463
464 /* An array can't have been allocated by new, so complain. */
465 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (exp)) == ARRAY_TYPE)
466 warning (0, "deleting array %q#E", exp);
467
468 t = build_expr_type_conversion (WANT_POINTER, exp, true);
469
470 if (t == NULL_TREE || t == error_mark_node)
471 {
472 error ("type %q#T argument given to %<delete%>, expected pointer",
473 TREE_TYPE (exp));
474 return error_mark_node;
475 }
476
477 type = TREE_TYPE (t);
478
479 /* As of Valley Forge, you can delete a pointer to const. */
480
481 /* You can't delete functions. */
482 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (type)) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
483 {
484 error ("cannot delete a function. Only pointer-to-objects are "
485 "valid arguments to %<delete%>");
486 return error_mark_node;
487 }
488
489 /* Deleting ptr to void is undefined behavior [expr.delete/3]. */
490 if (VOID_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (type)))
491 {
492 warning (OPT_Wdelete_incomplete, "deleting %qT is undefined", type);
493 doing_vec = 0;
494 }
495
496 /* Deleting a pointer with the value zero is valid and has no effect. */
497 if (integer_zerop (t))
498 return build1 (NOP_EXPR, void_type_node, t);
499
500 if (doing_vec)
501 return build_vec_delete (t, /*maxindex=*/NULL_TREE,
502 sfk_deleting_destructor,
503 use_global_delete, complain);
504 else
505 return build_delete (type, t, sfk_deleting_destructor,
506 LOOKUP_NORMAL, use_global_delete,
507 complain);
508}

510/* Report an error if the indicated template declaration is not the
511 sort of thing that should be a member template. */
512
513void
514check_member_template (tree tmpl)
515{
516 tree decl;
517
518 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (tmpl) == TEMPLATE_DECL);
519 decl = DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (tmpl);
520
521 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
522 || DECL_ALIAS_TEMPLATE_P (tmpl)
523 || (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL
524 && MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (decl))))
525 {
526 /* The parser rejects template declarations in local classes
527 (with the exception of generic lambdas). */
528 gcc_assert (!current_function_decl || LAMBDA_FUNCTION_P (decl));
529 /* The parser rejects any use of virtual in a function template. */
530 gcc_assert (!(TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
531 && DECL_VIRTUAL_P (decl)));
532
533 /* The debug-information generating code doesn't know what to do
534 with member templates. */
535 DECL_IGNORED_P (tmpl) = 1;
536 }
537 else if (variable_template_p (tmpl))
538 /* OK */;
539 else
540 error ("template declaration of %q#D", decl);
541}
542
543/* Sanity check: report error if this function FUNCTION is not
544 really a member of the class (CTYPE) it is supposed to belong to.
545 TEMPLATE_PARMS is used to specify the template parameters of a member
546 template passed as FUNCTION_DECL. If the member template is passed as a
547 TEMPLATE_DECL, it can be NULL since the parameters can be extracted
548 from the declaration. If the function is not a function template, it
549 must be NULL.
550 It returns the original declaration for the function, NULL_TREE if
551 no declaration was found, error_mark_node if an error was emitted. */
552
553tree
554check_classfn (tree ctype, tree function, tree template_parms)
555{
556 int ix;
557 bool is_template;
558 tree pushed_scope;
559
560 if (DECL_USE_TEMPLATE (function)
561 && !(TREE_CODE (function) == TEMPLATE_DECL
562 && DECL_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION (function))
563 && DECL_MEMBER_TEMPLATE_P (DECL_TI_TEMPLATE (function)))
564 /* Since this is a specialization of a member template,
565 we're not going to find the declaration in the class.
566 For example, in:
567
568 struct S { template <typename T> void f(T); };
569 template <> void S::f(int);
570
571 we're not going to find `S::f(int)', but there's no
572 reason we should, either. We let our callers know we didn't
573 find the method, but we don't complain. */
574 return NULL_TREE;
575
576 /* Basic sanity check: for a template function, the template parameters
577 either were not passed, or they are the same of DECL_TEMPLATE_PARMS. */
578 if (TREE_CODE (function) == TEMPLATE_DECL)
579 {
580 if (template_parms
581 && !comp_template_parms (template_parms,
582 DECL_TEMPLATE_PARMS (function)))
583 {
584 error ("template parameter lists provided don%'t match the "
585 "template parameters of %qD", function);
586 return error_mark_node;
587 }
588 template_parms = DECL_TEMPLATE_PARMS (function);
589 }
590
591 /* OK, is this a definition of a member template? */
592 is_template = (template_parms != NULL_TREE);
593
594 /* [temp.mem]
595
596 A destructor shall not be a member template. */
597 if (DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (function) && is_template)
598 {
599 error ("destructor %qD declared as member template", function);
600 return error_mark_node;
601 }
602
603 /* We must enter the scope here, because conversion operators are
604 named by target type, and type equivalence relies on typenames
605 resolving within the scope of CTYPE. */
606 pushed_scope = push_scope (ctype);
607 ix = class_method_index_for_fn (complete_type (ctype), function);
608 if (ix >= 0)
609 {
610 vec<tree, va_gc> *methods = CLASSTYPE_METHOD_VEC (ctype);
611 tree fndecls, fndecl = 0;
612 bool is_conv_op;
613 const char *format = NULL;
614
615 for (fndecls = (*methods)[ix];
616 fndecls; fndecls = OVL_NEXT (fndecls))
617 {
618 tree p1, p2;
619
620 fndecl = OVL_CURRENT (fndecls);
621 p1 = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (function));
622 p2 = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (fndecl));
623
624 /* We cannot simply call decls_match because this doesn't
625 work for static member functions that are pretending to
626 be methods, and because the name may have been changed by
627 asm("new_name"). */
628
629 /* Get rid of the this parameter on functions that become
630 static. */
631 if (DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (fndecl)
632 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (function)) == METHOD_TYPE)
633 p1 = TREE_CHAIN (p1);
634
635 /* A member template definition only matches a member template
636 declaration. */
637 if (is_template != (TREE_CODE (fndecl) == TEMPLATE_DECL))
638 continue;
639
640 /* ref-qualifier or absence of same must match. */
641 if (type_memfn_rqual (TREE_TYPE (function))
642 != type_memfn_rqual (TREE_TYPE (fndecl)))
643 continue;
644
645 // Include constraints in the match.
646 tree c1 = get_constraints (function);
647 tree c2 = get_constraints (fndecl);
648
649 /* While finding a match, same types and params are not enough
650 if the function is versioned. Also check version ("target")
651 attributes. */
652 if (same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (function)),
653 TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (fndecl)))
654 && compparms (p1, p2)
655 && !targetm.target_option.function_versions (function, fndecl)
656 && (!is_template
657 || comp_template_parms (template_parms,
658 DECL_TEMPLATE_PARMS (fndecl)))
659 && equivalent_constraints (c1, c2)
660 && (DECL_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION (function)
661 == DECL_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION (fndecl))
662 && (!DECL_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION (function)
663 || (DECL_TI_TEMPLATE (function)
664 == DECL_TI_TEMPLATE (fndecl))))
665 break;
666 }
667 if (fndecls)
668 {
669 if (pushed_scope)
670 pop_scope (pushed_scope);
671 return OVL_CURRENT (fndecls);
672 }
673
674 error_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (function),
675 "prototype for %q#D does not match any in class %qT",
676 function, ctype);
677 is_conv_op = DECL_CONV_FN_P (fndecl);
678
679 if (is_conv_op)
680 ix = CLASSTYPE_FIRST_CONVERSION_SLOT;
681 fndecls = (*methods)[ix];
682 while (fndecls)
683 {
684 fndecl = OVL_CURRENT (fndecls);
685 fndecls = OVL_NEXT (fndecls);
686
687 if (!fndecls && is_conv_op)
688 {
689 if (methods->length () > (size_t) ++ix)
690 {
691 fndecls = (*methods)[ix];
692 if (!DECL_CONV_FN_P (OVL_CURRENT (fndecls)))
693 {
694 fndecls = NULL_TREE;
695 is_conv_op = false;
696 }
697 }
698 else
699 is_conv_op = false;
700 }
701 if (format)
702 format = " %+#D";
703 else if (fndecls)
704 format = N_("candidates are: %+#D");
705 else
706 format = N_("candidate is: %+#D");
707 error (format, fndecl);
708 }
709 }
710 else if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (ctype))
711 cxx_incomplete_type_error (function, ctype);
712 else
713 error ("no %q#D member function declared in class %qT",
714 function, ctype);
715
716 if (pushed_scope)
717 pop_scope (pushed_scope);
718 return error_mark_node;
719}

721/* DECL is a function with vague linkage. Remember it so that at the
722 end of the translation unit we can decide whether or not to emit
723 it. */
724
725void
726note_vague_linkage_fn (tree decl)
727{
728 DECL_DEFER_OUTPUT (decl) = 1;
729 vec_safe_push (deferred_fns, decl);
730}

733

735note_variable_template_instantiation (tree decl)

737 vec_safe_push (pending_statics, decl);

740/* We have just processed the DECL, which is a static data member.
741 The other parameters are as for cp_finish_decl. */
742
743void
744finish_static_data_member_decl (tree decl,
745 tree init, bool init_const_expr_p,
746 tree asmspec_tree,
747 int flags)
748{
749 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = current_class_type;
750
751 /* We cannot call pushdecl here, because that would fill in the
752 TREE_CHAIN of our decl. Instead, we modify cp_finish_decl to do
753 the right thing, namely, to put this decl out straight away. */
754
755 if (! processing_template_decl)
756 vec_safe_push (pending_statics, decl);
757
758 if (LOCAL_CLASS_P (current_class_type)
759 /* We already complained about the template definition. */
760 && !DECL_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATION (decl))
761 permerror (input_location, "local class %q#T shall not have static data member %q#D",
762 current_class_type, decl);
763 else
764 for (tree t = current_class_type; TYPE_P (t);
765 t = CP_TYPE_CONTEXT (t))
766 if (TYPE_UNNAMED_P (t))
767 {
768 if (permerror (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
769 "static data member %qD in unnamed class", decl))
770 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (TYPE_NAME (t)),
771 "unnamed class defined here");
772 break;
773 }
774
775 DECL_IN_AGGR_P (decl) = 1;
776
777 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (decl)) == ARRAY_TYPE
778 && TYPE_DOMAIN (TREE_TYPE (decl)) == NULL_TREE)
779 SET_VAR_HAD_UNKNOWN_BOUND (decl);
780
781 cp_finish_decl (decl, init, init_const_expr_p, asmspec_tree, flags);
782}
783
784/* DECLARATOR and DECLSPECS correspond to a class member. The other
785 parameters are as for cp_finish_decl. Return the DECL for the
786 class member declared. */
787
788tree
789grokfield (const cp_declarator *declarator,
790 cp_decl_specifier_seq *declspecs,
791 tree init, bool init_const_expr_p,
792 tree asmspec_tree,
793 tree attrlist)
794{
795 tree value;
796 const char *asmspec = 0;
797 int flags;
798 tree name;
799
800 if (init
801 && TREE_CODE (init) == TREE_LIST
802 && TREE_VALUE (init) == error_mark_node
803 && TREE_CHAIN (init) == NULL_TREE)
804 init = NULL_TREE;
805
806 value = grokdeclarator (declarator, declspecs, FIELD, init != 0, &attrlist);
807 if (! value || value == error_mark_node)
808 /* friend or constructor went bad. */
809 return error_mark_node;
810 if (TREE_TYPE (value) == error_mark_node)
811 return value;
812
813 if (TREE_CODE (value) == TYPE_DECL && init)
814 {
815 error ("typedef %qD is initialized (use decltype instead)", value);
816 init = NULL_TREE;
817 }
818
819 /* Pass friendly classes back. */
820 if (value == void_type_node)
821 return value;
822
823
824 name = DECL_NAME (value);
825
826 if (name != NULL_TREE)
827 {
828 if (TREE_CODE (name) == TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR)
829 {
830 error ("explicit template argument list not allowed");
831 return error_mark_node;
832 }
833
834 if (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (name)[0] == '_'
835 && ! strcmp (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (name), "_vptr"))
836 error ("member %qD conflicts with virtual function table field name",
837 value);
838 }
839
840 /* Stash away type declarations. */
841 if (TREE_CODE (value) == TYPE_DECL)
842 {
843 DECL_NONLOCAL (value) = 1;
844 DECL_CONTEXT (value) = current_class_type;
845
846 if (attrlist)
847 {
848 int attrflags = 0;
849
850 /* If this is a typedef that names the class for linkage purposes
851 (7.1.3p8), apply any attributes directly to the type. */
852 if (OVERLOAD_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (value))
853 && value == TYPE_NAME (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (value))))
854 attrflags = ATTR_FLAG_TYPE_IN_PLACE;
855
856 cplus_decl_attributes (&value, attrlist, attrflags);
857 }
858
859 if (decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_typedef)
860 && TREE_TYPE (value) != error_mark_node
861 && TYPE_NAME (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (value))) != value)
862 set_underlying_type (value);
863
864 /* It's important that push_template_decl below follows
865 set_underlying_type above so that the created template
866 carries the properly set type of VALUE. */
867 if (processing_template_decl)
868 value = push_template_decl (value);
869
870 record_locally_defined_typedef (value);
871 return value;
872 }
873
874 int friendp = decl_spec_seq_has_spec_p (declspecs, ds_friend);
875
876 if (!friendp && DECL_IN_AGGR_P (value))
877 {
878 error ("%qD is already defined in %qT", value, DECL_CONTEXT (value));
879 return void_type_node;
880 }
881
882 if (asmspec_tree && asmspec_tree != error_mark_node)
883 asmspec = TREE_STRING_POINTER (asmspec_tree);
884
885 if (init)
886 {
887 if (TREE_CODE (value) == FUNCTION_DECL)
888 {
889 if (init == ridpointers[(int)RID_DELETE])
890 {
891 if (friendp && decl_defined_p (value))
892 {
893 error ("redefinition of %q#D", value);
894 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (value),
895 "%q#D previously defined here", value);
896 }
897 else
898 {
899 DECL_DELETED_FN (value) = 1;
900 DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (value) = 1;
901 DECL_INITIAL (value) = error_mark_node;
902 }
903 }
904 else if (init == ridpointers[(int)RID_DEFAULT])
905 {
906 if (defaultable_fn_check (value))
907 {
908 DECL_DEFAULTED_FN (value) = 1;
909 DECL_INITIALIZED_IN_CLASS_P (value) = 1;
910 DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (value) = 1;
911 }
912 }
913 else if (TREE_CODE (init) == DEFAULT_ARG)
914 error ("invalid initializer for member function %qD", value);
915 else if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (value)) == METHOD_TYPE)
916 {
917 if (integer_zerop (init))
918 DECL_PURE_VIRTUAL_P (value) = 1;
919 else if (error_operand_p (init))
920 ; /* An error has already been reported. */
921 else
922 error ("invalid initializer for member function %qD",
923 value);
924 }
925 else
926 {
927 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (value)) == FUNCTION_TYPE);
928 if (friendp)
929 error ("initializer specified for friend function %qD",
930 value);
931 else
932 error ("initializer specified for static member function %qD",
933 value);
934 }
935 }
936 else if (TREE_CODE (value) == FIELD_DECL)
937 /* C++11 NSDMI, keep going. */;
938 else if (!VAR_P (value))
939 gcc_unreachable ();
940 }
941
942 /* Pass friend decls back. */
943 if ((TREE_CODE (value) == FUNCTION_DECL
944 || TREE_CODE (value) == TEMPLATE_DECL)
945 && DECL_CONTEXT (value) != current_class_type)
946 return value;
947
948 /* Need to set this before push_template_decl. */
949 if (VAR_P (value))
950 DECL_CONTEXT (value) = current_class_type;
951
952 if (processing_template_decl && VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (value))
953 {
954 value = push_template_decl (value);
955 if (error_operand_p (value))
956 return error_mark_node;
957 }
958
959 if (attrlist)
960 cplus_decl_attributes (&value, attrlist, 0);
961
962 if (init && DIRECT_LIST_INIT_P (init))
963 flags = LOOKUP_NORMAL;
964 else
965 flags = LOOKUP_IMPLICIT;
966
967 switch (TREE_CODE (value))
968 {
969 case VAR_DECL:
970 finish_static_data_member_decl (value, init, init_const_expr_p,
971 asmspec_tree, flags);
972 return value;
973
974 case FIELD_DECL:
975 if (asmspec)
976 error ("%<asm%> specifiers are not permitted on non-static data members");
977 if (DECL_INITIAL (value) == error_mark_node)
978 init = error_mark_node;
979 cp_finish_decl (value, init, /*init_const_expr_p=*/false,
980 NULL_TREE, flags);
981 DECL_IN_AGGR_P (value) = 1;
982 return value;
983
984 case FUNCTION_DECL:
985 if (asmspec)
986 set_user_assembler_name (value, asmspec);
987
988 cp_finish_decl (value,
989 /*init=*/NULL_TREE,
990 /*init_const_expr_p=*/false,
991 asmspec_tree, flags);
992
993 /* Pass friends back this way. */
994 if (DECL_FRIEND_P (value))
995 return void_type_node;
996
997 DECL_IN_AGGR_P (value) = 1;
998 return value;
999
1000 default:
1001 gcc_unreachable ();
1002 }
1003 return NULL_TREE;
1004}
1005
1006/* Like `grokfield', but for bitfields.
1007 WIDTH is non-NULL for bit fields only, and is an INTEGER_CST node. */
1008
1009tree
1010grokbitfield (const cp_declarator *declarator,
1011 cp_decl_specifier_seq *declspecs, tree width,
1012 tree attrlist)
1013{
1014 tree value = grokdeclarator (declarator, declspecs, BITFIELD, 0, &attrlist);
1015
1016 if (value == error_mark_node)
1017 return NULL_TREE; /* friends went bad. */
1018 if (TREE_TYPE (value) == error_mark_node)
1019 return value;
1020
1021 /* Pass friendly classes back. */
1022 if (VOID_TYPE_P (value))
1023 return void_type_node;
1024
1025 if (!INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (value))
1026 && (POINTER_TYPE_P (value)
1027 || !dependent_type_p (TREE_TYPE (value))))
1028 {
1029 error ("bit-field %qD with non-integral type", value);
1030 return error_mark_node;
1031 }
1032
1033 if (TREE_CODE (value) == TYPE_DECL)
1034 {
1035 error ("cannot declare %qD to be a bit-field type", value);
1036 return NULL_TREE;
1037 }
1038
1039 /* Usually, finish_struct_1 catches bitfields with invalid types.
1040 But, in the case of bitfields with function type, we confuse
1041 ourselves into thinking they are member functions, so we must
1042 check here. */
1043 if (TREE_CODE (value) == FUNCTION_DECL)
1044 {
1045 error ("cannot declare bit-field %qD with function type",
1046 DECL_NAME (value));
1047 return NULL_TREE;
1048 }
1049
1050 if (DECL_IN_AGGR_P (value))
1051 {
1052 error ("%qD is already defined in the class %qT", value,
1053 DECL_CONTEXT (value));
1054 return void_type_node;
1055 }
1056
1057 if (TREE_STATIC (value))
1058 {
1059 error ("static member %qD cannot be a bit-field", value);
1060 return NULL_TREE;
1061 }
1062 cp_finish_decl (value, NULL_TREE, false, NULL_TREE, 0);
1063
1064 if (width != error_mark_node)
1065 {
1066 /* The width must be an integer type. */
1067 if (!type_dependent_expression_p (width)
1068 && !INTEGRAL_OR_UNSCOPED_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (width)))
1069 error ("width of bit-field %qD has non-integral type %qT", value,
1070 TREE_TYPE (width));
1071 else
1072 {
1073 DECL_INITIAL (value) = width;
1074 SET_DECL_C_BIT_FIELD (value);
1075 }
1076 }
1077
1078 DECL_IN_AGGR_P (value) = 1;
1079
1080 if (attrlist)
1081 cplus_decl_attributes (&value, attrlist, /*flags=*/0);
1082
1083 return value;
1084}

1087/* Returns true iff ATTR is an attribute which needs to be applied at
1088 instantiation time rather than template definition time. */
1089
1090static bool
1091is_late_template_attribute (tree attr, tree decl)
1092{
1093 tree name = get_attribute_name (attr);
1094 tree args = TREE_VALUE (attr);
1095 const struct attribute_spec *spec = lookup_attribute_spec (name);
1096 tree arg;
1097
1098 if (!spec)
1099 /* Unknown attribute. */
1100 return false;
1101
1102 /* Attribute weak handling wants to write out assembly right away. */
1103 if (is_attribute_p ("weak", name))
1104 return true;
1105
1106 /* Attributes used and unused are applied directly, as they appertain to
1107 decls. */
1108 if (is_attribute_p ("unused", name)
1109 || is_attribute_p ("used", name))
1110 return false;
1111
1112 /* Attribute tls_model wants to modify the symtab. */
1113 if (is_attribute_p ("tls_model", name))
1114 return true;
1115
1116 /* #pragma omp declare simd attribute needs to be always deferred. */
1117 if (flag_openmp
1118 && is_attribute_p ("omp declare simd", name))
1119 return true;
1120
1121 /* An attribute pack is clearly dependent. */
1122 if (args && PACK_EXPANSION_P (args))
1123 return true;
1124
1125 /* If any of the arguments are dependent expressions, we can't evaluate
1126 the attribute until instantiation time. */
1127 for (arg = args; arg; arg = TREE_CHAIN (arg))
1128 {
1129 tree t = TREE_VALUE (arg);
1130
1131 /* If the first attribute argument is an identifier, only consider
1132 second and following arguments. Attributes like mode, format,
1133 cleanup and several target specific attributes aren't late
1134 just because they have an IDENTIFIER_NODE as first argument. */
1135 if (arg == args && attribute_takes_identifier_p (name)
1136 && identifier_p (t))
1137 continue;
1138
1139 if (value_dependent_expression_p (t)
1140 || type_dependent_expression_p (t))
1141 return true;
1142 }
1143
1144 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL
1145 || TYPE_P (decl)
1146 || spec->type_required)
1147 {
1148 tree type = TYPE_P (decl) ? decl : TREE_TYPE (decl);
1149
1150 /* We can't apply any attributes to a completely unknown type until
1151 instantiation time. */
1152 enum tree_code code = TREE_CODE (type);
1153 if (code == TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM
1154 || code == BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM
1155 || code == TYPENAME_TYPE)
1156 return true;
1157 /* Also defer most attributes on dependent types. This is not
1158 necessary in all cases, but is the better default. */
1159 else if (dependent_type_p (type)
1160 /* But some attributes specifically apply to templates. */
1161 && !is_attribute_p ("abi_tag", name)
1162 && !is_attribute_p ("deprecated", name)
1163 && !is_attribute_p ("visibility", name))
1164 return true;
1165 else
1166 return false;
1167 }
1168 else
1169 return false;
1170}
1171
1172/* ATTR_P is a list of attributes. Remove any attributes which need to be
1173 applied at instantiation time and return them. If IS_DEPENDENT is true,
1174 the declaration itself is dependent, so all attributes should be applied
1175 at instantiation time. */
1176
1177static tree
1178splice_template_attributes (tree *attr_p, tree decl)
1179{
1180 tree *p = attr_p;
1181 tree late_attrs = NULL_TREE;
1182 tree *q = &late_attrs;
1183
1184 if (!p)
1185 return NULL_TREE;
1186
1187 for (; *p; )
1188 {
1189 if (is_late_template_attribute (*p, decl))
1190 {
1191 ATTR_IS_DEPENDENT (*p) = 1;
1192 *q = *p;
1193 *p = TREE_CHAIN (*p);
1194 q = &TREE_CHAIN (*q);
1195 *q = NULL_TREE;
1196 }
1197 else
1198 p = &TREE_CHAIN (*p);
1199 }
1200
1201 return late_attrs;
1202}
1203
1204/* Remove any late attributes from the list in ATTR_P and attach them to
1205 DECL_P. */
1206
1207static void
1208save_template_attributes (tree *attr_p, tree *decl_p)
1209{
1210 tree *q;
1211
1212 if (attr_p && *attr_p == error_mark_node)
1213 return;
1214
1215 tree late_attrs = splice_template_attributes (attr_p, *decl_p);
1216 if (!late_attrs)
1217 return;
1218
1219 if (DECL_P (*decl_p))
1220 q = &DECL_ATTRIBUTES (*decl_p);
1221 else
1222 q = &TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (*decl_p);
1223
1224 tree old_attrs = *q;
1225
1226 /* Merge the late attributes at the beginning with the attribute
1227 list. */
1228 late_attrs = merge_attributes (late_attrs, *q);
1229 *q = late_attrs;
1230
1231 if (!DECL_P (*decl_p) && *decl_p == TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (*decl_p))
1232 {
1233 /* We've added new attributes directly to the main variant, so
1234 now we need to update all of the other variants to include
1235 these new attributes. */
1236 tree variant;
1237 for (variant = TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT (*decl_p); variant;
1238 variant = TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT (variant))
1239 {
1240 gcc_assert (TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (variant) == old_attrs);
1241 TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (variant) = TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (*decl_p);
1242 }
1243 }
1244}
1245
1246/* True if ATTRS contains any dependent attributes that affect type
1247 identity. */
1248
1249bool
1250any_dependent_type_attributes_p (tree attrs)
1251{
1252 for (tree a = attrs; a; a = TREE_CHAIN (a))
1253 if (ATTR_IS_DEPENDENT (a))
1254 {
1255 const attribute_spec *as = lookup_attribute_spec (TREE_PURPOSE (a));
1256 if (as && as->affects_type_identity)
1257 return true;
1258 }
1259 return false;
1260}
1261
1262/* Return true iff ATTRS are acceptable attributes to be applied in-place
1263 to a typedef which gives a previously unnamed class or enum a name for
1264 linkage purposes. */
1265
1266bool
1267attributes_naming_typedef_ok (tree attrs)
1268{
1269 for (; attrs; attrs = TREE_CHAIN (attrs))
1270 {
1271 tree name = get_attribute_name (attrs);
1272 if (is_attribute_p ("vector_size", name))
1273 return false;
1274 }
1275 return true;
1276}
1277
1278/* Like reconstruct_complex_type, but handle also template trees. */
1279
1280tree
1281cp_reconstruct_complex_type (tree type, tree bottom)
1282{
1283 tree inner, outer;
1284 bool late_return_type_p = false;
1285
1286 if (TYPE_PTR_P (type))
1287 {
1288 inner = cp_reconstruct_complex_type (TREE_TYPE (type), bottom);
1289 outer = build_pointer_type_for_mode (inner, TYPE_MODE (type),
1290 TYPE_REF_CAN_ALIAS_ALL (type));
1291 }
1292 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
1293 {
1294 inner = cp_reconstruct_complex_type (TREE_TYPE (type), bottom);
1295 outer = build_reference_type_for_mode (inner, TYPE_MODE (type),
1296 TYPE_REF_CAN_ALIAS_ALL (type));
1297 }
1298 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
1299 {
1300 inner = cp_reconstruct_complex_type (TREE_TYPE (type), bottom);
1301 outer = build_cplus_array_type (inner, TYPE_DOMAIN (type));
1302 /* Don't call cp_build_qualified_type on ARRAY_TYPEs, the
1303 element type qualification will be handled by the recursive
1304 cp_reconstruct_complex_type call and cp_build_qualified_type
1305 for ARRAY_TYPEs changes the element type. */
1306 return outer;
1307 }
1308 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
1309 {
1310 late_return_type_p = TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE (type);
1311 inner = cp_reconstruct_complex_type (TREE_TYPE (type), bottom);
1312 outer = build_function_type (inner, TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type));
1313 outer = apply_memfn_quals (outer,
1314 type_memfn_quals (type),
1315 type_memfn_rqual (type));
1316 }
1317 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
1318 {
1319 late_return_type_p = TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE (type);
1320 inner = cp_reconstruct_complex_type (TREE_TYPE (type), bottom);
1321 /* The build_method_type_directly() routine prepends 'this' to argument list,
1322 so we must compensate by getting rid of it. */
1323 outer
1324 = build_method_type_directly
1325 (class_of_this_parm (type), inner,
1326 TREE_CHAIN (TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type)));
1327 }
1328 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == OFFSET_TYPE)
1329 {
1330 inner = cp_reconstruct_complex_type (TREE_TYPE (type), bottom);
1331 outer = build_offset_type (TYPE_OFFSET_BASETYPE (type), inner);
1332 }
1333 else
1334 return bottom;
1335
1336 if (TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (type))
1337 outer = cp_build_type_attribute_variant (outer, TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (type));
1338 outer = cp_build_qualified_type (outer, cp_type_quals (type));
1339
1340 if (late_return_type_p)
1341 TYPE_HAS_LATE_RETURN_TYPE (outer) = 1;
1342
1343 return outer;
1344}
1345
1346/* Replaces any constexpr expression that may be into the attributes
1347 arguments with their reduced value. */
1348
1349static void
1350cp_check_const_attributes (tree attributes)
1351{
1352 if (attributes == error_mark_node)
1353 return;
1354
1355 tree attr;
1356 for (attr = attributes; attr; attr = TREE_CHAIN (attr))
1357 {
1358 tree arg;
1359 for (arg = TREE_VALUE (attr); arg; arg = TREE_CHAIN (arg))
1360 {
1361 tree expr = TREE_VALUE (arg);
1362 if (EXPR_P (expr))
1363 TREE_VALUE (arg) = fold_non_dependent_expr (expr);
1364 }
1365 }
1366}
1367
1368/* Return true if TYPE is an OpenMP mappable type. */
1369bool
1370cp_omp_mappable_type (tree type)
1371{
1372 /* Mappable type has to be complete. */
1373 if (type == error_mark_node || !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type))
1374 return false;
1375 /* Arrays have mappable type if the elements have mappable type. */
1376 while (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
1377 type = TREE_TYPE (type);
1378 /* A mappable type cannot contain virtual members. */
1379 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type) && CLASSTYPE_VTABLES (type))
1380 return false;
1381 /* All data members must be non-static. */
1382 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
1383 {
1384 tree field;
1385 for (field = TYPE_FIELDS (type); field; field = DECL_CHAIN (field))
1386 if (VAR_P (field))
1387 return false;
1388 /* All fields must have mappable types. */
1389 else if (TREE_CODE (field) == FIELD_DECL
1390 && !cp_omp_mappable_type (TREE_TYPE (field)))
1391 return false;
1392 }
1393 return true;
1394}
1395
1396/* Like decl_attributes, but handle C++ complexity. */
1397
1398void
1399cplus_decl_attributes (tree *decl, tree attributes, int flags)
1400{
1401 if (*decl == NULL_TREE || *decl == void_type_node
1402 || *decl == error_mark_node)
1403 return;
1404
1405 /* Add implicit "omp declare target" attribute if requested. */
1406 if (scope_chain->omp_declare_target_attribute
1407 && ((VAR_P (*decl)
1408 && (TREE_STATIC (*decl) || DECL_EXTERNAL (*decl)))
1409 || TREE_CODE (*decl) == FUNCTION_DECL))
1410 {
1411 if (VAR_P (*decl)
1412 && DECL_CLASS_SCOPE_P (*decl))
1413 error ("%q+D static data member inside of declare target directive",
1414 *decl);
1415 else if (!processing_template_decl
1416 && VAR_P (*decl)
1417 && !cp_omp_mappable_type (TREE_TYPE (*decl)))
1418 error ("%q+D in declare target directive does not have mappable type",
1419 *decl);
1420 else
1421 attributes = tree_cons (get_identifier ("omp declare target"),
1422 NULL_TREE, attributes);
1423 }
1424
1425 if (processing_template_decl)
1426 {
1427 if (check_for_bare_parameter_packs (attributes))
1428 return;
1429
1430 save_template_attributes (&attributes, decl);
1431 }
1432
1433 cp_check_const_attributes (attributes);
1434
1435 if (TREE_CODE (*decl) == TEMPLATE_DECL)
1436 decl = &DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (*decl);
1437
1438 if (TREE_TYPE (*decl) && TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (TREE_TYPE (*decl)))
1439 {
1440 attributes
1441 = decl_attributes (decl, attributes, flags | ATTR_FLAG_FUNCTION_NEXT);
1442 decl_attributes (&TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FN_TYPE_RAW (TREE_TYPE (*decl)),
1443 attributes, flags);
1444 }
1445 else
1446 decl_attributes (decl, attributes, flags);
1447
1448 if (TREE_CODE (*decl) == TYPE_DECL)
1449 SET_IDENTIFIER_TYPE_VALUE (DECL_NAME (*decl), TREE_TYPE (*decl));
1450
1451 /* Propagate deprecation out to the template. */
1452 if (TREE_DEPRECATED (*decl))
1453 if (tree ti = get_template_info (*decl))
1454 {
1455 tree tmpl = TI_TEMPLATE (ti);
1456 tree pattern = (TYPE_P (*decl) ? TREE_TYPE (tmpl)
1457 : DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (tmpl));
1458 if (*decl == pattern)
1459 TREE_DEPRECATED (tmpl) = true;
1460 }
1461}
1462
1463/* Walks through the namespace- or function-scope anonymous union
1464 OBJECT, with the indicated TYPE, building appropriate VAR_DECLs.
1465 Returns one of the fields for use in the mangled name. */
1466
1467static tree
1468build_anon_union_vars (tree type, tree object)
1469{
1470 tree main_decl = NULL_TREE;
1471 tree field;
1472
1473 /* Rather than write the code to handle the non-union case,
1474 just give an error. */
1475 if (TREE_CODE (type) != UNION_TYPE)
1476 {
1477 error ("anonymous struct not inside named type");
1478 return error_mark_node;
1479 }
1480
1481 for (field = TYPE_FIELDS (type);
1482 field != NULL_TREE;
1483 field = DECL_CHAIN (field))
1484 {
1485 tree decl;
1486 tree ref;
1487
1488 if (DECL_ARTIFICIAL (field))
1489 continue;
1490 if (TREE_CODE (field) != FIELD_DECL)
1491 {
1492 permerror (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (field),
1493 "%q#D invalid; an anonymous union can only "
1494 "have non-static data members", field);
1495 continue;
1496 }
1497
1498 if (TREE_PRIVATE (field))
1499 permerror (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (field),
1500 "private member %q#D in anonymous union", field);
1501 else if (TREE_PROTECTED (field))
1502 permerror (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (field),
1503 "protected member %q#D in anonymous union", field);
1504
1505 if (processing_template_decl)
1506 ref = build_min_nt_loc (UNKNOWN_LOCATION, COMPONENT_REF, object,
1507 DECL_NAME (field), NULL_TREE);
1508 else
1509 ref = build_class_member_access_expr (object, field, NULL_TREE,
1510 false, tf_warning_or_error);
1511
1512 if (DECL_NAME (field))
1513 {
1514 tree base;
1515
1516 decl = build_decl (input_location,
1517 VAR_DECL, DECL_NAME (field), TREE_TYPE (field));
1518 DECL_ANON_UNION_VAR_P (decl) = 1;
1519 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl) = 1;
1520
1521 base = get_base_address (object);
1522 TREE_PUBLIC (decl) = TREE_PUBLIC (base);
1523 TREE_STATIC (decl) = TREE_STATIC (base);
1524 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = DECL_EXTERNAL (base);
1525
1526 SET_DECL_VALUE_EXPR (decl, ref);
1527 DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (decl) = 1;
1528
1529 decl = pushdecl (decl);
1530 }
1531 else if (ANON_AGGR_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (field)))
1532 decl = build_anon_union_vars (TREE_TYPE (field), ref);
1533 else
1534 decl = 0;
1535
1536 if (main_decl == NULL_TREE)
1537 main_decl = decl;
1538 }
1539
1540 return main_decl;
1541}
1542
1543/* Finish off the processing of a UNION_TYPE structure. If the union is an
1544 anonymous union, then all members must be laid out together. PUBLIC_P
1545 is nonzero if this union is not declared static. */
1546
1547void
1548finish_anon_union (tree anon_union_decl)
1549{
1550 tree type;
1551 tree main_decl;
1552 bool public_p;
1553
1554 if (anon_union_decl == error_mark_node)
1555 return;
1556
1557 type = TREE_TYPE (anon_union_decl);
1558 public_p = TREE_PUBLIC (anon_union_decl);
1559
1560 /* The VAR_DECL's context is the same as the TYPE's context. */
1561 DECL_CONTEXT (anon_union_decl) = DECL_CONTEXT (TYPE_NAME (type));
1562
1563 if (TYPE_FIELDS (type) == NULL_TREE)
1564 return;
1565
1566 if (public_p)
1567 {
1568 error ("namespace-scope anonymous aggregates must be static");
1569 return;
1570 }
1571
1572 main_decl = build_anon_union_vars (type, anon_union_decl);
1573 if (main_decl == error_mark_node)
1574 return;
1575 if (main_decl == NULL_TREE)
1576 {
1577 warning (0, "anonymous union with no members");
1578 return;
1579 }
1580
1581 if (!processing_template_decl)
1582 {
1583 /* Use main_decl to set the mangled name. */
1584 DECL_NAME (anon_union_decl) = DECL_NAME (main_decl);
1585 maybe_commonize_var (anon_union_decl);
1586 if (TREE_STATIC (anon_union_decl) || DECL_EXTERNAL (anon_union_decl))
1587 mangle_decl (anon_union_decl);
1588 DECL_NAME (anon_union_decl) = NULL_TREE;
1589 }
1590
1591 pushdecl (anon_union_decl);
1592 cp_finish_decl (anon_union_decl, NULL_TREE, false, NULL_TREE, 0);
1593}
1594
1595/* Auxiliary functions to make type signatures for
1596 `operator new' and `operator delete' correspond to
1597 what compiler will be expecting. */
1598
1599tree
1600coerce_new_type (tree type)
1601{
1602 int e = 0;
1603 tree args = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type);
1604
1605 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE);
1606
1607 if (!same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (type), ptr_type_node))
1608 {
1609 e = 1;
1610 error ("%<operator new%> must return type %qT", ptr_type_node);
1611 }
1612
1613 if (args && args != void_list_node)
1614 {
1615 if (TREE_PURPOSE (args))
1616 {
1617 /* [basic.stc.dynamic.allocation]
1618
1619 The first parameter shall not have an associated default
1620 argument. */
1621 error ("the first parameter of %<operator new%> cannot "
1622 "have a default argument");
1623 /* Throw away the default argument. */
1624 TREE_PURPOSE (args) = NULL_TREE;
1625 }
1626
1627 if (!same_type_p (TREE_VALUE (args), size_type_node))
1628 {
1629 e = 2;
1630 args = TREE_CHAIN (args);
1631 }
1632 }
1633 else
1634 e = 2;
1635
1636 if (e == 2)
1637 permerror (input_location, "%<operator new%> takes type %<size_t%> (%qT) "
1638 "as first parameter", size_type_node);
1639
1640 switch (e)
1641 {
1642 case 2:
1643 args = tree_cons (NULL_TREE, size_type_node, args);
1644 /* Fall through. */
1645 case 1:
1646 type = build_exception_variant
1647 (build_function_type (ptr_type_node, args),
1648 TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (type));
1649 /* Fall through. */
1650 default:;
1651 }
1652 return type;
1653}
1654
1655tree
1656coerce_delete_type (tree type)
1657{
1658 int e = 0;
1659 tree args = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type);
1660
1661 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE);
1662
1663 if (!same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (type), void_type_node))
1664 {
1665 e = 1;
1666 error ("%<operator delete%> must return type %qT", void_type_node);
1667 }
1668
1669 if (!args || args == void_list_node
1670 || !same_type_p (TREE_VALUE (args), ptr_type_node))
1671 {
1672 e = 2;
1673 if (args && args != void_list_node)
1674 args = TREE_CHAIN (args);
1675 error ("%<operator delete%> takes type %qT as first parameter",
1676 ptr_type_node);
1677 }
1678 switch (e)
1679 {
1680 case 2:
1681 args = tree_cons (NULL_TREE, ptr_type_node, args);
1682 /* Fall through. */
1683 case 1:
1684 type = build_exception_variant
1685 (build_function_type (void_type_node, args),
1686 TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (type));
1687 /* Fall through. */
1688 default:;
1689 }
1690
1691 return type;
1692}
1693
1694/* DECL is a VAR_DECL for a vtable: walk through the entries in the vtable
1695 and mark them as needed. */
1696
1697static void
1698mark_vtable_entries (tree decl)
1699{
1700 tree fnaddr;
1701 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT idx;
1702
1703 /* It's OK for the vtable to refer to deprecated virtual functions. */
1704 warning_sentinel w(warn_deprecated_decl);
1705
1706 FOR_EACH_CONSTRUCTOR_VALUE (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (DECL_INITIAL (decl)),
1707 idx, fnaddr)
1708 {
1709 tree fn;
1710
1711 STRIP_NOPS (fnaddr);
1712
1713 if (TREE_CODE (fnaddr) != ADDR_EXPR
1714 && TREE_CODE (fnaddr) != FDESC_EXPR)
1715 /* This entry is an offset: a virtual base class offset, a
1716 virtual call offset, an RTTI offset, etc. */
1717 continue;
1718
1719 fn = TREE_OPERAND (fnaddr, 0);
1720 TREE_ADDRESSABLE (fn) = 1;
1721 /* When we don't have vcall offsets, we output thunks whenever
1722 we output the vtables that contain them. With vcall offsets,
1723 we know all the thunks we'll need when we emit a virtual
1724 function, so we emit the thunks there instead. */
1725 if (DECL_THUNK_P (fn))
1726 use_thunk (fn, /*emit_p=*/0);
1727 mark_used (fn);
1728 }
1729}
1730
1731/* Set DECL up to have the closest approximation of "initialized common"
1732 linkage available. */
1733
1734void
1735comdat_linkage (tree decl)
1736{
1737 if (flag_weak)
1738 make_decl_one_only (decl, cxx_comdat_group (decl));
1739 else if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
1740 || (VAR_P (decl) && DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl)))
1741 /* We can just emit function and compiler-generated variables
1742 statically; having multiple copies is (for the most part) only
1743 a waste of space.
1744
1745 There are two correctness issues, however: the address of a
1746 template instantiation with external linkage should be the
1747 same, independent of what translation unit asks for the
1748 address, and this will not hold when we emit multiple copies of
1749 the function. However, there's little else we can do.
1750
1751 Also, by default, the typeinfo implementation assumes that
1752 there will be only one copy of the string used as the name for
1753 each type. Therefore, if weak symbols are unavailable, the
1754 run-time library should perform a more conservative check; it
1755 should perform a string comparison, rather than an address
1756 comparison. */
1757 TREE_PUBLIC (decl) = 0;
1758 else
1759 {
1760 /* Static data member template instantiations, however, cannot
1761 have multiple copies. */
1762 if (DECL_INITIAL (decl) == 0
1763 || DECL_INITIAL (decl) == error_mark_node)
1764 DECL_COMMON (decl) = 1;
1765 else if (EMPTY_CONSTRUCTOR_P (DECL_INITIAL (decl)))
1766 {
1767 DECL_COMMON (decl) = 1;
1768 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = error_mark_node;
1769 }
1770 else if (!DECL_EXPLICIT_INSTANTIATION (decl))
1771 {
1772 /* We can't do anything useful; leave vars for explicit
1773 instantiation. */
1774 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 1;
1775 DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (decl) = 0;
1776 }
1777 }
1778
1779 if (TREE_PUBLIC (decl))
1780 DECL_COMDAT (decl) = 1;
1781}
1782
1783/* For win32 we also want to put explicit instantiations in
1784 linkonce sections, so that they will be merged with implicit
1785 instantiations; otherwise we get duplicate symbol errors.
1786 For Darwin we do not want explicit instantiations to be
1787 linkonce. */
1788
1789void
1790maybe_make_one_only (tree decl)
1791{
1792 /* We used to say that this was not necessary on targets that support weak
1793 symbols, because the implicit instantiations will defer to the explicit
1794 one. However, that's not actually the case in SVR4; a strong definition
1795 after a weak one is an error. Also, not making explicit
1796 instantiations one_only means that we can end up with two copies of
1797 some template instantiations. */
1798 if (! flag_weak)
1799 return;
1800
1801 /* We can't set DECL_COMDAT on functions, or cp_finish_file will think
1802 we can get away with not emitting them if they aren't used. We need
1803 to for variables so that cp_finish_decl will update their linkage,
1804 because their DECL_INITIAL may not have been set properly yet. */
1805
1806 if (!TARGET_WEAK_NOT_IN_ARCHIVE_TOC
1807 || (! DECL_EXPLICIT_INSTANTIATION (decl)
1808 && ! DECL_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION (decl)))
1809 {
1810 make_decl_one_only (decl, cxx_comdat_group (decl));
1811
1812 if (VAR_P (decl))
1813 {
1814 varpool_node *node = varpool_node::get_create (decl);
1815 DECL_COMDAT (decl) = 1;
1816 /* Mark it needed so we don't forget to emit it. */
1817 node->forced_by_abi = true;
1818 TREE_USED (decl) = 1;
1819 }
1820 }
1821}
1822
1823/* Returns true iff DECL, a FUNCTION_DECL or VAR_DECL, has vague linkage.
1824 This predicate will give the right answer during parsing of the
1825 function, which other tests may not. */
1826
1827bool
1828vague_linkage_p (tree decl)
1829{
1830 if (!TREE_PUBLIC (decl))
1831 {
1832 /* maybe_thunk_body clears TREE_PUBLIC and DECL_ABSTRACT_P on the
1833 maybe-in-charge 'tor variants; in that case we need to check one of
1834 the "clones" for the real linkage. But only in that case; before
1835 maybe_clone_body we haven't yet copied the linkage to the clones. */
1836 if ((DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_DESTRUCTOR_P (decl)
1837 || DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_CONSTRUCTOR_P (decl))
1838 && !DECL_ABSTRACT_P (decl)
1839 && DECL_CHAIN (decl)
1840 && DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION (DECL_CHAIN (decl)))
1841 return vague_linkage_p (DECL_CHAIN (decl));
1842
1843 gcc_checking_assert (!DECL_COMDAT (decl));
1844 return false;
1845 }
1846 /* Unfortunately, import_export_decl has not always been called
1847 before the function is processed, so we cannot simply check
1848 DECL_COMDAT. */
1849 if (DECL_COMDAT (decl)
1850 || (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
1851 && DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl))
1852 || (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl)
1853 && DECL_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATION (decl))
1854 || (VAR_P (decl) && DECL_INLINE_VAR_P (decl)))
1855 return true;
1856 else if (DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (decl))
1857 /* A local static in an inline effectively has vague linkage. */
1858 return (TREE_STATIC (decl)
1859 && vague_linkage_p (DECL_CONTEXT (decl)));
1860 else
1861 return false;
1862}
1863
1864/* Determine whether or not we want to specifically import or export CTYPE,
1865 using various heuristics. */
1866
1867static void
1868import_export_class (tree ctype)
1869{
1870 /* -1 for imported, 1 for exported. */
1871 int import_export = 0;
1872
1873 /* It only makes sense to call this function at EOF. The reason is
1874 that this function looks at whether or not the first non-inline
1875 non-abstract virtual member function has been defined in this
1876 translation unit. But, we can't possibly know that until we've
1877 seen the entire translation unit. */
1878 gcc_assert (at_eof);
1879
1880 if (CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_KNOWN (ctype))
1881 return;
1882
1883 /* If MULTIPLE_SYMBOL_SPACES is set and we saw a #pragma interface,
1884 we will have CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_ONLY set but not
1885 CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_KNOWN. In that case, we don't want to use this
1886 heuristic because someone will supply a #pragma implementation
1887 elsewhere, and deducing it here would produce a conflict. */
1888 if (CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_ONLY (ctype))
1889 return;
1890
1891 if (lookup_attribute ("dllimport", TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (ctype)))
1892 import_export = -1;
1893 else if (lookup_attribute ("dllexport", TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (ctype)))
1894 import_export = 1;
1895 else if (CLASSTYPE_IMPLICIT_INSTANTIATION (ctype)
1896 && !flag_implicit_templates)
1897 /* For a template class, without -fimplicit-templates, check the
1898 repository. If the virtual table is assigned to this
1899 translation unit, then export the class; otherwise, import
1900 it. */
1901 import_export = repo_export_class_p (ctype) ? 1 : -1;
1902 else if (TYPE_POLYMORPHIC_P (ctype))
1903 {
1904 /* The ABI specifies that the virtual table and associated
1905 information are emitted with the key method, if any. */
1906 tree method = CLASSTYPE_KEY_METHOD (ctype);
1907 /* If weak symbol support is not available, then we must be
1908 careful not to emit the vtable when the key function is
1909 inline. An inline function can be defined in multiple
1910 translation units. If we were to emit the vtable in each
1911 translation unit containing a definition, we would get
1912 multiple definition errors at link-time. */
1913 if (method && (flag_weak || ! DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (method)))
1914 import_export = (DECL_REALLY_EXTERN (method) ? -1 : 1);
1915 }
1916
1917 /* When MULTIPLE_SYMBOL_SPACES is set, we cannot count on seeing
1918 a definition anywhere else. */
1919 if (MULTIPLE_SYMBOL_SPACES && import_export == -1)
1920 import_export = 0;
1921
1922 /* Allow back ends the chance to overrule the decision. */
1923 if (targetm.cxx.import_export_class)
1924 import_export = targetm.cxx.import_export_class (ctype, import_export);
1925
1926 if (import_export)
1927 {
1928 SET_CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_KNOWN (ctype);
1929 CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_ONLY (ctype) = (import_export < 0);
1930 }
1931}

1933/* Return true if VAR has already been provided to the back end; in that
1934 case VAR should not be modified further by the front end. */
1935static bool
1936var_finalized_p (tree var)
1937{
1938 return varpool_node::get_create (var)->definition;
1939}
1940
1941/* DECL is a VAR_DECL or FUNCTION_DECL which, for whatever reason,
1942 must be emitted in this translation unit. Mark it as such. */
1943
1944void
1945mark_needed (tree decl)
1946{
1947 TREE_USED (decl) = 1;
1948 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
1949 {
1950 /* Extern inline functions don't become needed when referenced.
1951 If we know a method will be emitted in other TU and no new
1952 functions can be marked reachable, just use the external
1953 definition. */
1954 struct cgraph_node *node = cgraph_node::get_create (decl);
1955 node->forced_by_abi = true;
1956
1957 /* #pragma interface and -frepo code can call mark_needed for
1958 maybe-in-charge 'tors; mark the clones as well. */
1959 tree clone;
1960 FOR_EACH_CLONE (clone, decl)
1961 mark_needed (clone);
1962 }
1963 else if (VAR_P (decl))
1964 {
1965 varpool_node *node = varpool_node::get_create (decl);
1966 /* C++ frontend use mark_decl_references to force COMDAT variables
1967 to be output that might appear dead otherwise. */
1968 node->forced_by_abi = true;
1969 }
1970}
1971
1972/* DECL is either a FUNCTION_DECL or a VAR_DECL. This function
1973 returns true if a definition of this entity should be provided in
1974 this object file. Callers use this function to determine whether
1975 or not to let the back end know that a definition of DECL is
1976 available in this translation unit. */
1977
1978bool
1979decl_needed_p (tree decl)
1980{
1981 gcc_assert (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (decl));
1982 /* This function should only be called at the end of the translation
1983 unit. We cannot be sure of whether or not something will be
1984 COMDAT until that point. */
1985 gcc_assert (at_eof);
1986
1987 /* All entities with external linkage that are not COMDAT/EXTERN should be
1988 emitted; they may be referred to from other object files. */
1989 if (TREE_PUBLIC (decl) && !DECL_COMDAT (decl) && !DECL_REALLY_EXTERN (decl))
1990 return true;
1991 /* Functions marked "dllexport" must be emitted so that they are
1992 visible to other DLLs. */
1993 if (flag_keep_inline_dllexport
1994 && lookup_attribute ("dllexport", DECL_ATTRIBUTES (decl)))
1995 return true;
1996
1997 /* When not optimizing, do not bother to produce definitions for extern
1998 symbols. */
1999 if (DECL_REALLY_EXTERN (decl)
2000 && ((TREE_CODE (decl) != FUNCTION_DECL
2001 && !optimize)
2002 || (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
2003 && !opt_for_fn (decl, optimize)))
2004 && !lookup_attribute ("always_inline", decl))
2005 return false;
2006
2007 /* If this entity was used, let the back end see it; it will decide
2008 whether or not to emit it into the object file. */
2009 if (TREE_USED (decl))
2010 return true;
2011 /* Virtual functions might be needed for devirtualization. */
2012 if (flag_devirtualize
2013 && TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
2014 && DECL_VIRTUAL_P (decl))
2015 return true;
2016 /* Otherwise, DECL does not need to be emitted -- yet. A subsequent
2017 reference to DECL might cause it to be emitted later. */
2018 return false;
2019}
2020
2021/* If necessary, write out the vtables for the dynamic class CTYPE.
2022 Returns true if any vtables were emitted. */
2023
2024static bool
2025maybe_emit_vtables (tree ctype)
2026{
2027 tree vtbl;
2028 tree primary_vtbl;
2029 int needed = 0;
2030 varpool_node *current = NULL, *last = NULL;
2031
2032 /* If the vtables for this class have already been emitted there is
2033 nothing more to do. */
2034 primary_vtbl = CLASSTYPE_VTABLES (ctype);
2035 if (var_finalized_p (primary_vtbl))
2036 return false;
2037 /* Ignore dummy vtables made by get_vtable_decl. */
2038 if (TREE_TYPE (primary_vtbl) == void_type_node)
2039 return false;
2040
2041 /* On some targets, we cannot determine the key method until the end
2042 of the translation unit -- which is when this function is
2043 called. */
2044 if (!targetm.cxx.key_method_may_be_inline ())
2045 determine_key_method (ctype);
2046
2047 /* See if any of the vtables are needed. */
2048 for (vtbl = CLASSTYPE_VTABLES (ctype); vtbl; vtbl = DECL_CHAIN (vtbl))
2049 {
2050 import_export_decl (vtbl);
2051 if (DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (vtbl) && decl_needed_p (vtbl))
2052 needed = 1;
2053 }
2054 if (!needed)
2055 {
2056 /* If the references to this class' vtables are optimized away,
2057 still emit the appropriate debugging information. See
2058 dfs_debug_mark. */
2059 if (DECL_COMDAT (primary_vtbl)
2060 && CLASSTYPE_DEBUG_REQUESTED (ctype))
2061 note_debug_info_needed (ctype);
2062 return false;
2063 }
2064
2065 /* The ABI requires that we emit all of the vtables if we emit any
2066 of them. */
2067 for (vtbl = CLASSTYPE_VTABLES (ctype); vtbl; vtbl = DECL_CHAIN (vtbl))
2068 {
2069 /* Mark entities references from the virtual table as used. */
2070 mark_vtable_entries (vtbl);
2071
2072 if (TREE_TYPE (DECL_INITIAL (vtbl)) == 0)
2073 {
2074 vec<tree, va_gc> *cleanups = NULL;
2075 tree expr = store_init_value (vtbl, DECL_INITIAL (vtbl), &cleanups,
2076 LOOKUP_NORMAL);
2077
2078 /* It had better be all done at compile-time. */
2079 gcc_assert (!expr && !cleanups);
2080 }
2081
2082 /* Write it out. */
2083 DECL_EXTERNAL (vtbl) = 0;
2084 rest_of_decl_compilation (vtbl, 1, 1);
2085
2086 /* Because we're only doing syntax-checking, we'll never end up
2087 actually marking the variable as written. */
2088 if (flag_syntax_only)
2089 TREE_ASM_WRITTEN (vtbl) = 1;
2090 else if (DECL_ONE_ONLY (vtbl))
2091 {
2092 current = varpool_node::get_create (vtbl);
2093 if (last)
2094 current->add_to_same_comdat_group (last);
2095 last = current;
2096 }
2097 }
2098
2099 /* Since we're writing out the vtable here, also write the debug
2100 info. */
2101 note_debug_info_needed (ctype);
2102
2103 return true;
2104}

2106/* A special return value from type_visibility meaning internal
2107 linkage. */
2108
2109enum { VISIBILITY_ANON = VISIBILITY_INTERNAL+1 };
2110
2111/* walk_tree helper function for type_visibility. */
2112
2113static tree
2114min_vis_r (tree *tp, int *walk_subtrees, void *data)
2115{
2116 int *vis_p = (int *)data;
2117 if (! TYPE_P (*tp))
2118 {
2119 *walk_subtrees = 0;
2120 }
2121 else if (OVERLOAD_TYPE_P (*tp)
2122 && !TREE_PUBLIC (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (*tp)))
2123 {
2124 *vis_p = VISIBILITY_ANON;
2125 return *tp;
2126 }
2127 else if (CLASS_TYPE_P (*tp)
2128 && CLASSTYPE_VISIBILITY (*tp) > *vis_p)
2129 *vis_p = CLASSTYPE_VISIBILITY (*tp);
2130 return NULL;
2131}
2132
2133/* Returns the visibility of TYPE, which is the minimum visibility of its
2134 component types. */
2135
2136static int
2137type_visibility (tree type)
2138{
2139 int vis = VISIBILITY_DEFAULT;
2140 cp_walk_tree_without_duplicates (&type, min_vis_r, &vis);
2141 return vis;
2142}

2144/* Limit the visibility of DECL to VISIBILITY, if not explicitly
2145 specified (or if VISIBILITY is static). If TMPL is true, this
2146 constraint is for a template argument, and takes precedence
2147 over explicitly-specified visibility on the template. */
2148
2149static void
2150constrain_visibility (tree decl, int visibility, bool tmpl)
2151{
2152 if (visibility == VISIBILITY_ANON)
2153 {
2154 /* extern "C" declarations aren't affected by the anonymous
2155 namespace. */
2156 if (!DECL_EXTERN_C_P (decl))
2157 {
2158 TREE_PUBLIC (decl) = 0;
2159 DECL_WEAK (decl) = 0;
2160 DECL_COMMON (decl) = 0;
2161 DECL_COMDAT (decl) = false;
2162 if (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (decl))
2163 {
2164 struct symtab_node *snode = symtab_node::get (decl);
2165
2166 if (snode)
2167 snode->set_comdat_group (NULL);
2168 }
2169 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl) = 1;
2170 if (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl))
2171 DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (decl) = 1;
2172 }
2173 }
2174 else if (visibility > DECL_VISIBILITY (decl)
2175 && (tmpl || !DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl)))
2176 {
2177 DECL_VISIBILITY (decl) = (enum symbol_visibility) visibility;
2178 /* This visibility was not specified. */
2179 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl) = false;
2180 }
2181}
2182
2183/* Constrain the visibility of DECL based on the visibility of its template
2184 arguments. */
2185
2186static void
2187constrain_visibility_for_template (tree decl, tree targs)
2188{
2189 /* If this is a template instantiation, check the innermost
2190 template args for visibility constraints. The outer template
2191 args are covered by the class check. */
2192 tree args = INNERMOST_TEMPLATE_ARGS (targs);
2193 int i;
2194 for (i = TREE_VEC_LENGTH (args); i > 0; --i)
2195 {
2196 int vis = 0;
2197
2198 tree arg = TREE_VEC_ELT (args, i-1);
2199 if (TYPE_P (arg))
2200 vis = type_visibility (arg);
2201 else
2202 {
2203 if (REFERENCE_REF_P (arg))
2204 arg = TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0);
2205 if (TREE_TYPE (arg))
2206 STRIP_NOPS (arg);
2207 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == ADDR_EXPR)
2208 arg = TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0);
2209 if (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (arg))
2210 {
2211 if (! TREE_PUBLIC (arg))
2212 vis = VISIBILITY_ANON;
2213 else
2214 vis = DECL_VISIBILITY (arg);
2215 }
2216 }
2217 if (vis)
2218 constrain_visibility (decl, vis, true);
2219 }
2220}
2221
2222/* Like c_determine_visibility, but with additional C++-specific
2223 behavior.
2224
2225 Function-scope entities can rely on the function's visibility because
2226 it is set in start_preparsed_function.
2227
2228 Class-scope entities cannot rely on the class's visibility until the end
2229 of the enclosing class definition.
2230
2231 Note that because namespaces have multiple independent definitions,
2232 namespace visibility is handled elsewhere using the #pragma visibility
2233 machinery rather than by decorating the namespace declaration.
2234
2235 The goal is for constraints from the type to give a diagnostic, and
2236 other constraints to be applied silently. */
2237
2238void
2239determine_visibility (tree decl)
2240{
2241 /* Remember that all decls get VISIBILITY_DEFAULT when built. */
2242
2243 /* Only relevant for names with external linkage. */
2244 if (!TREE_PUBLIC (decl))
2245 return;
2246
2247 /* Cloned constructors and destructors get the same visibility as
2248 the underlying function. That should be set up in
2249 maybe_clone_body. */
2250 gcc_assert (!DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (decl));
2251
2252 bool orig_visibility_specified = DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl);
2253 enum symbol_visibility orig_visibility = DECL_VISIBILITY (decl);
2254
2255 /* The decl may be a template instantiation, which could influence
2256 visibilty. */
2257 tree template_decl = NULL_TREE;
2258 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL)
2259 {
2260 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
2261 {
2262 if (CLASSTYPE_USE_TEMPLATE (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
2263 template_decl = decl;
2264 }
2265 else if (TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
2266 template_decl = decl;
2267 }
2268 else if (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl) && DECL_USE_TEMPLATE (decl))
2269 template_decl = decl;
2270
2271 /* If DECL is a member of a class, visibility specifiers on the
2272 class can influence the visibility of the DECL. */
2273 tree class_type = NULL_TREE;
2274 if (DECL_CLASS_SCOPE_P (decl))
2275 class_type = DECL_CONTEXT (decl);
2276 else
2277 {
2278 /* Not a class member. */
2279
2280 /* Virtual tables have DECL_CONTEXT set to their associated class,
2281 so they are automatically handled above. */
2282 gcc_assert (!VAR_P (decl)
2283 || !DECL_VTABLE_OR_VTT_P (decl));
2284
2285 if (DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (decl) && ! DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl))
2286 {
2287 /* Local statics and classes get the visibility of their
2288 containing function by default, except that
2289 -fvisibility-inlines-hidden doesn't affect them. */
2290 tree fn = DECL_CONTEXT (decl);
2291 if (DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (fn))
2292 {
2293 DECL_VISIBILITY (decl) = DECL_VISIBILITY (fn);
2294 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl) =
2295 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (fn);
2296 }
2297 else
2298 {
2299 if (DECL_CLASS_SCOPE_P (fn))
2300 determine_visibility_from_class (decl, DECL_CONTEXT (fn));
2301 else if (determine_hidden_inline (fn))
2302 {
2303 DECL_VISIBILITY (decl) = default_visibility;
2304 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl) =
2305 visibility_options.inpragma;
2306 }
2307 else
2308 {
2309 DECL_VISIBILITY (decl) = DECL_VISIBILITY (fn);
2310 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl) =
2311 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (fn);
2312 }
2313 }
2314
2315 /* Local classes in templates have CLASSTYPE_USE_TEMPLATE set,
2316 but have no TEMPLATE_INFO, so don't try to check it. */
2317 template_decl = NULL_TREE;
2318 }
2319 else if (VAR_P (decl) && DECL_TINFO_P (decl)
2320 && flag_visibility_ms_compat)
2321 {
2322 /* Under -fvisibility-ms-compat, types are visible by default,
2323 even though their contents aren't. */
2324 tree underlying_type = TREE_TYPE (DECL_NAME (decl));
2325 int underlying_vis = type_visibility (underlying_type);
2326 if (underlying_vis == VISIBILITY_ANON
2327 || (CLASS_TYPE_P (underlying_type)
2328 && CLASSTYPE_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (underlying_type)))
2329 constrain_visibility (decl, underlying_vis, false);
2330 else
2331 DECL_VISIBILITY (decl) = VISIBILITY_DEFAULT;
2332 }
2333 else if (VAR_P (decl) && DECL_TINFO_P (decl))
2334 {
2335 /* tinfo visibility is based on the type it's for. */
2336 constrain_visibility
2337 (decl, type_visibility (TREE_TYPE (DECL_NAME (decl))), false);
2338
2339 /* Give the target a chance to override the visibility associated
2340 with DECL. */
2341 if (TREE_PUBLIC (decl)
2342 && !DECL_REALLY_EXTERN (decl)
2343 && CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (DECL_NAME (decl)))
2344 && !CLASSTYPE_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (TREE_TYPE (DECL_NAME (decl))))
2345 targetm.cxx.determine_class_data_visibility (decl);
2346 }
2347 else if (template_decl)
2348 /* Template instantiations and specializations get visibility based
2349 on their template unless they override it with an attribute. */;
2350 else if (! DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl))
2351 {
2352 if (determine_hidden_inline (decl))
2353 DECL_VISIBILITY (decl) = VISIBILITY_HIDDEN;
2354 else
2355 {
2356 /* Set default visibility to whatever the user supplied with
2357 #pragma GCC visibility or a namespace visibility attribute. */
2358 DECL_VISIBILITY (decl) = default_visibility;
2359 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl) = visibility_options.inpragma;
2360 }
2361 }
2362 }
2363
2364 if (template_decl)
2365 {
2366 /* If the specialization doesn't specify visibility, use the
2367 visibility from the template. */
2368 tree tinfo = get_template_info (template_decl);
2369 tree args = TI_ARGS (tinfo);
2370 tree attribs = (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL
2371 ? TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (TREE_TYPE (decl))
2372 : DECL_ATTRIBUTES (decl));
2373
2374 if (args != error_mark_node)
2375 {
2376 tree pattern = DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (TI_TEMPLATE (tinfo));
2377
2378 if (!DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl))
2379 {
2380 if (!DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (pattern)
2381 && determine_hidden_inline (decl))
2382 DECL_VISIBILITY (decl) = VISIBILITY_HIDDEN;
2383 else
2384 {
2385 DECL_VISIBILITY (decl) = DECL_VISIBILITY (pattern);
2386 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl)
2387 = DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (pattern);
2388 }
2389 }
2390
2391 if (args
2392 /* Template argument visibility outweighs #pragma or namespace
2393 visibility, but not an explicit attribute. */
2394 && !lookup_attribute ("visibility", attribs))
2395 {
2396 int depth = TMPL_ARGS_DEPTH (args);
2397 if (DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl))
2398 {
2399 /* A class template member with explicit visibility
2400 overrides the class visibility, so we need to apply
2401 all the levels of template args directly. */
2402 int i;
2403 for (i = 1; i <= depth; ++i)
2404 {
2405 tree lev = TMPL_ARGS_LEVEL (args, i);
2406 constrain_visibility_for_template (decl, lev);
2407 }
2408 }
2409 else if (PRIMARY_TEMPLATE_P (TI_TEMPLATE (tinfo)))
2410 /* Limit visibility based on its template arguments. */
2411 constrain_visibility_for_template (decl, args);
2412 }
2413 }
2414 }
2415
2416 if (class_type)
2417 determine_visibility_from_class (decl, class_type);
2418
2419 if (decl_anon_ns_mem_p (decl))
2420 /* Names in an anonymous namespace get internal linkage.
2421 This might change once we implement export. */
2422 constrain_visibility (decl, VISIBILITY_ANON, false);
2423 else if (TREE_CODE (decl) != TYPE_DECL)
2424 {
2425 /* Propagate anonymity from type to decl. */
2426 int tvis = type_visibility (TREE_TYPE (decl));
2427 if (tvis == VISIBILITY_ANON
2428 || ! DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl))
2429 constrain_visibility (decl, tvis, false);
2430 }
2431 else if (no_linkage_check (TREE_TYPE (decl), /*relaxed_p=*/true))
2432 /* DR 757: A type without linkage shall not be used as the type of a
2433 variable or function with linkage, unless
2434 o the variable or function has extern "C" linkage (7.5 [dcl.link]), or
2435 o the variable or function is not used (3.2 [basic.def.odr]) or is
2436 defined in the same translation unit.
2437
2438 Since non-extern "C" decls need to be defined in the same
2439 translation unit, we can make the type internal. */
2440 constrain_visibility (decl, VISIBILITY_ANON, false);
2441
2442 /* If visibility changed and DECL already has DECL_RTL, ensure
2443 symbol flags are updated. */
2444 if ((DECL_VISIBILITY (decl) != orig_visibility
2445 || DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl) != orig_visibility_specified)
2446 && ((VAR_P (decl) && TREE_STATIC (decl))
2447 || TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
2448 && DECL_RTL_SET_P (decl))
2449 make_decl_rtl (decl);
2450}
2451
2452/* By default, static data members and function members receive
2453 the visibility of their containing class. */
2454
2455static void
2456determine_visibility_from_class (tree decl, tree class_type)
2457{
2458 if (DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl))
2459 return;
2460
2461 if (determine_hidden_inline (decl))
2462 DECL_VISIBILITY (decl) = VISIBILITY_HIDDEN;
2463 else
2464 {
2465 /* Default to the class visibility. */
2466 DECL_VISIBILITY (decl) = CLASSTYPE_VISIBILITY (class_type);
2467 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl)
2468 = CLASSTYPE_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (class_type);
2469 }
2470
2471 /* Give the target a chance to override the visibility associated
2472 with DECL. */
2473 if (VAR_P (decl)
2474 && (DECL_TINFO_P (decl)
2475 || (DECL_VTABLE_OR_VTT_P (decl)
2476 /* Construction virtual tables are not exported because
2477 they cannot be referred to from other object files;
2478 their name is not standardized by the ABI. */
2479 && !DECL_CONSTRUCTION_VTABLE_P (decl)))
2480 && TREE_PUBLIC (decl)
2481 && !DECL_REALLY_EXTERN (decl)
2482 && !CLASSTYPE_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (class_type))
2483 targetm.cxx.determine_class_data_visibility (decl);
2484}

2486/* Returns true iff DECL is an inline that should get hidden visibility
2487 because of -fvisibility-inlines-hidden. */
2488
2489static bool
2490determine_hidden_inline (tree decl)
2491{
2492 return (visibility_options.inlines_hidden
2493 /* Don't do this for inline templates; specializations might not be
2494 inline, and we don't want them to inherit the hidden
2495 visibility. We'll set it here for all inline instantiations. */
2496 && !processing_template_decl
2497 && TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
2498 && DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl)
2499 && (! DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl)
2500 || ! DECL_EXPLICIT_INSTANTIATION (decl)));
2501}

2503/* Constrain the visibility of a class TYPE based on the visibility of its
2504 field types. Warn if any fields require lesser visibility. */
2505
2506void
2507constrain_class_visibility (tree type)
2508{
2509 tree binfo;
2510 tree t;
2511 int i;
2512
2513 int vis = type_visibility (type);
2514
2515 if (vis == VISIBILITY_ANON
2516 || DECL_IN_SYSTEM_HEADER (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (type)))
2517 return;
2518
2519 /* Don't warn about visibility if the class has explicit visibility. */
2520 if (CLASSTYPE_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (type))
2521 vis = VISIBILITY_INTERNAL;
2522
2523 for (t = TYPE_FIELDS (type); t; t = DECL_CHAIN (t))
2524 if (TREE_CODE (t) == FIELD_DECL && TREE_TYPE (t) != error_mark_node)
2525 {
2526 tree ftype = strip_pointer_or_array_types (TREE_TYPE (t));
2527 int subvis = type_visibility (ftype);
2528
2529 if (subvis == VISIBILITY_ANON)
2530 {
2531 if (!in_main_input_context())
2532 {
2533 tree nlt = no_linkage_check (ftype, /*relaxed_p=*/false);
2534 if (nlt)
2535 {
2536 if (same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (t), nlt))
2537 warning (OPT_Wsubobject_linkage, "\
2538%qT has a field %qD whose type has no linkage",
2539 type, t);
2540 else
2541 warning (OPT_Wsubobject_linkage, "\
2542%qT has a field %qD whose type depends on the type %qT which has no linkage",
2543 type, t, nlt);
2544 }
2545 else
2546 warning (OPT_Wsubobject_linkage, "\
2547%qT has a field %qD whose type uses the anonymous namespace",
2548 type, t);
2549 }
2550 }
2551 else if (MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (ftype)
2552 && vis < VISIBILITY_HIDDEN
2553 && subvis >= VISIBILITY_HIDDEN)
2554 warning (OPT_Wattributes, "\
2555%qT declared with greater visibility than the type of its field %qD",
2556 type, t);
2557 }
2558
2559 binfo = TYPE_BINFO (type);
2560 for (i = 0; BINFO_BASE_ITERATE (binfo, i, t); ++i)
2561 {
2562 int subvis = type_visibility (TREE_TYPE (t));
2563
2564 if (subvis == VISIBILITY_ANON)
2565 {
2566 if (!in_main_input_context())
2567 {
2568 tree nlt = no_linkage_check (TREE_TYPE (t), /*relaxed_p=*/false);
2569 if (nlt)
2570 {
2571 if (same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (t), nlt))
2572 warning (OPT_Wsubobject_linkage, "\
2573%qT has a base %qT whose type has no linkage",
2574 type, TREE_TYPE (t));
2575 else
2576 warning (OPT_Wsubobject_linkage, "\
2577%qT has a base %qT whose type depends on the type %qT which has no linkage",
2578 type, TREE_TYPE (t), nlt);
2579 }
2580 else
2581 warning (OPT_Wsubobject_linkage, "\
2582%qT has a base %qT whose type uses the anonymous namespace",
2583 type, TREE_TYPE (t));
2584 }
2585 }
2586 else if (vis < VISIBILITY_HIDDEN
2587 && subvis >= VISIBILITY_HIDDEN)
2588 warning (OPT_Wattributes, "\
2589%qT declared with greater visibility than its base %qT",
2590 type, TREE_TYPE (t));
2591 }
2592}

2602

2604reset_type_linkage_1 (tree type)
