2617/* Then reset the visibility of any static data members or member
2618 functions that use those types. */
2619
2620static void
2621reset_decl_linkage (tree decl)
2622{
2623 if (TREE_PUBLIC (decl))
2624 return;
2625 if (DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (decl))
2626 return;
2627 TREE_PUBLIC (decl) = true;
2628 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl) = false;
2629 determine_visibility (decl);
2630 tentative_decl_linkage (decl);
2631}
2632static void
2633reset_type_linkage_2 (tree type)
2634{
2635 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
2636 {
2637 if (tree vt = CLASSTYPE_VTABLES (type))
2638 {
2639 tree name = mangle_vtbl_for_type (type);
2640 DECL_NAME (vt) = name;
2641 SET_DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (vt, name);
2642 reset_decl_linkage (vt);
2643 }
2644 if (tree ti = CLASSTYPE_TYPEINFO_VAR (type))
2645 {
2646 tree name = mangle_typeinfo_for_type (type);
2647 DECL_NAME (ti) = name;
2648 SET_DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (ti, name);
2649 TREE_TYPE (name) = type;
2650 reset_decl_linkage (ti);
2651 }
2652 for (tree m = TYPE_FIELDS (type); m; m = DECL_CHAIN (m))
2653 {
2654 tree mem = STRIP_TEMPLATE (m);
2655 if (VAR_P (mem))
2656 reset_decl_linkage (mem);
2657 }
2658 for (tree m = TYPE_METHODS (type); m; m = DECL_CHAIN (m))
2659 {
2660 tree mem = STRIP_TEMPLATE (m);
2661 reset_decl_linkage (mem);
2662 if (DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_CONSTRUCTOR_P (mem))
2663 {
2664 /* Also update its name, for cxx_dwarf_name. */
2665 DECL_NAME (mem) = TYPE_IDENTIFIER (type);
2666 if (m != mem)
2667 DECL_NAME (m) = TYPE_IDENTIFIER (type);
2668 }
2669 }
2670 binding_table_foreach (CLASSTYPE_NESTED_UTDS (type),
2671 bt_reset_linkage_2, NULL);
2672 }
2673}
2674static void
2675bt_reset_linkage_2 (binding_entry b, void */*data*/)
2676{
2677 reset_type_linkage_2 (b->type);
2678}
2679void
2680reset_type_linkage (tree type)
2681{
2682 reset_type_linkage_1 (type);
2683 reset_type_linkage_2 (type);
2684}

2686/* Set up our initial idea of what the linkage of DECL should be. */
2687
2688void
2689tentative_decl_linkage (tree decl)
2690{
2691 if (DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl))
2692 /* We've already made a decision as to how this function will
2693 be handled. */;
2694 else if (vague_linkage_p (decl))
2695 {
2696 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
2697 && decl_defined_p (decl))
2698 {
2699 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 1;
2700 DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (decl) = 1;
2701 note_vague_linkage_fn (decl);
2702 /* A non-template inline function with external linkage will
2703 always be COMDAT. As we must eventually determine the
2704 linkage of all functions, and as that causes writes to
2705 the data mapped in from the PCH file, it's advantageous
2706 to mark the functions at this point. */
2707 if (DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl)
2708 && (!DECL_IMPLICIT_INSTANTIATION (decl)
2709 || DECL_DEFAULTED_FN (decl)))
2710 {
2711 /* This function must have external linkage, as
2712 otherwise DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN would have been
2713 set. */
2714 gcc_assert (TREE_PUBLIC (decl));
2715 comdat_linkage (decl);
2716 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl) = 1;
2717 }
2718 }
2719 else if (VAR_P (decl))
2720 maybe_commonize_var (decl);
2721 }
2722}
2723
2724/* DECL is a FUNCTION_DECL or VAR_DECL. If the object file linkage
2725 for DECL has not already been determined, do so now by setting
2726 DECL_EXTERNAL, DECL_COMDAT and other related flags. Until this
2727 function is called entities with vague linkage whose definitions
2728 are available must have TREE_PUBLIC set.
2729
2730 If this function decides to place DECL in COMDAT, it will set
2731 appropriate flags -- but will not clear DECL_EXTERNAL. It is up to
2732 the caller to decide whether or not to clear DECL_EXTERNAL. Some
2733 callers defer that decision until it is clear that DECL is actually
2734 required. */
2735
2736void
2737import_export_decl (tree decl)
2738{
2739 int emit_p;
2740 bool comdat_p;
2741 bool import_p;
2742 tree class_type = NULL_TREE;
2743
2744 if (DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl))
2745 return;
2746
2747 /* We cannot determine what linkage to give to an entity with vague
2748 linkage until the end of the file. For example, a virtual table
2749 for a class will be defined if and only if the key method is
2750 defined in this translation unit. As a further example, consider
2751 that when compiling a translation unit that uses PCH file with
2752 "-frepo" it would be incorrect to make decisions about what
2753 entities to emit when building the PCH; those decisions must be
2754 delayed until the repository information has been processed. */
2755 gcc_assert (at_eof);
2756 /* Object file linkage for explicit instantiations is handled in
2757 mark_decl_instantiated. For static variables in functions with
2758 vague linkage, maybe_commonize_var is used.
2759
2760 Therefore, the only declarations that should be provided to this
2761 function are those with external linkage that are:
2762
2763 * implicit instantiations of function templates
2764
2765 * inline function
2766
2767 * implicit instantiations of static data members of class
2768 templates
2769
2770 * virtual tables
2771
2772 * typeinfo objects
2773
2774 Furthermore, all entities that reach this point must have a
2775 definition available in this translation unit.
2776
2777 The following assertions check these conditions. */
2778 gcc_assert (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (decl));
2779 /* Any code that creates entities with TREE_PUBLIC cleared should
2780 also set DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN. */
2781 gcc_assert (TREE_PUBLIC (decl));
2782 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
2783 gcc_assert (DECL_IMPLICIT_INSTANTIATION (decl)
2784 || DECL_FRIEND_PSEUDO_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATION (decl)
2785 || DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl));
2786 else
2787 gcc_assert (DECL_IMPLICIT_INSTANTIATION (decl)
2788 || DECL_VTABLE_OR_VTT_P (decl)
2789 || DECL_TINFO_P (decl));
2790 /* Check that a definition of DECL is available in this translation
2791 unit. */
2792 gcc_assert (!DECL_REALLY_EXTERN (decl));
2793
2794 /* Assume that DECL will not have COMDAT linkage. */
2795 comdat_p = false;
2796 /* Assume that DECL will not be imported into this translation
2797 unit. */
2798 import_p = false;
2799
2800 /* See if the repository tells us whether or not to emit DECL in
2801 this translation unit. */
2802 emit_p = repo_emit_p (decl);
2803 if (emit_p == 0)
2804 import_p = true;
2805 else if (emit_p == 1)
2806 {
2807 /* The repository indicates that this entity should be defined
2808 here. Make sure the back end honors that request. */
2809 mark_needed (decl);
2810 /* Output the definition as an ordinary strong definition. */
2811 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 0;
2812 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl) = 1;
2813 return;
2814 }
2815
2816 if (import_p)
2817 /* We have already decided what to do with this DECL; there is no
2818 need to check anything further. */
2819 ;
2820 else if (VAR_P (decl) && DECL_VTABLE_OR_VTT_P (decl))
2821 {
2822 class_type = DECL_CONTEXT (decl);
2823 import_export_class (class_type);
2824 if (CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_KNOWN (class_type)
2825 && CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_ONLY (class_type))
2826 import_p = true;
2827 else if ((!flag_weak || TARGET_WEAK_NOT_IN_ARCHIVE_TOC)
2828 && !CLASSTYPE_USE_TEMPLATE (class_type)
2829 && CLASSTYPE_KEY_METHOD (class_type)
2830 && !DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (CLASSTYPE_KEY_METHOD (class_type)))
2831 /* The ABI requires that all virtual tables be emitted with
2832 COMDAT linkage. However, on systems where COMDAT symbols
2833 don't show up in the table of contents for a static
2834 archive, or on systems without weak symbols (where we
2835 approximate COMDAT linkage by using internal linkage), the
2836 linker will report errors about undefined symbols because
2837 it will not see the virtual table definition. Therefore,
2838 in the case that we know that the virtual table will be
2839 emitted in only one translation unit, we make the virtual
2840 table an ordinary definition with external linkage. */
2841 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 0;
2842 else if (CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_KNOWN (class_type))
2843 {
2844 /* CLASS_TYPE is being exported from this translation unit,
2845 so DECL should be defined here. */
2846 if (!flag_weak && CLASSTYPE_EXPLICIT_INSTANTIATION (class_type))
2847 /* If a class is declared in a header with the "extern
2848 template" extension, then it will not be instantiated,
2849 even in translation units that would normally require
2850 it. Often such classes are explicitly instantiated in
2851 one translation unit. Therefore, the explicit
2852 instantiation must be made visible to other translation
2853 units. */
2854 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 0;
2855 else
2856 {
2857 /* The generic C++ ABI says that class data is always
2858 COMDAT, even if there is a key function. Some
2859 variants (e.g., the ARM EABI) says that class data
2860 only has COMDAT linkage if the class data might be
2861 emitted in more than one translation unit. When the
2862 key method can be inline and is inline, we still have
2863 to arrange for comdat even though
2864 class_data_always_comdat is false. */
2865 if (!CLASSTYPE_KEY_METHOD (class_type)
2866 || DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (CLASSTYPE_KEY_METHOD (class_type))
2867 || targetm.cxx.class_data_always_comdat ())
2868 {
2869 /* The ABI requires COMDAT linkage. Normally, we
2870 only emit COMDAT things when they are needed;
2871 make sure that we realize that this entity is
2872 indeed needed. */
2873 comdat_p = true;
2874 mark_needed (decl);
2875 }
2876 }
2877 }
2878 else if (!flag_implicit_templates
2879 && CLASSTYPE_IMPLICIT_INSTANTIATION (class_type))
2880 import_p = true;
2881 else
2882 comdat_p = true;
2883 }
2884 else if (VAR_P (decl) && DECL_TINFO_P (decl))
2885 {
2886 tree type = TREE_TYPE (DECL_NAME (decl));
2887 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
2888 {
2889 class_type = type;
2890 import_export_class (type);
2891 if (CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_KNOWN (type)
2892 && TYPE_POLYMORPHIC_P (type)
2893 && CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_ONLY (type)
2894 /* If -fno-rtti was specified, then we cannot be sure
2895 that RTTI information will be emitted with the
2896 virtual table of the class, so we must emit it
2897 wherever it is used. */
2898 && flag_rtti)
2899 import_p = true;
2900 else
2901 {
2902 if (CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_KNOWN (type)
2903 && !CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_ONLY (type))
2904 {
2905 comdat_p = (targetm.cxx.class_data_always_comdat ()
2906 || (CLASSTYPE_KEY_METHOD (type)
2907 && DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (CLASSTYPE_KEY_METHOD (type))));
2908 mark_needed (decl);
2909 if (!flag_weak)
2910 {
2911 comdat_p = false;
2912 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 0;
2913 }
2914 }
2915 else
2916 comdat_p = true;
2917 }
2918 }
2919 else
2920 comdat_p = true;
2921 }
2922 else if (DECL_TEMPLOID_INSTANTIATION (decl))
2923 {
2924 /* DECL is an implicit instantiation of a function or static
2925 data member. */
2926 if ((flag_implicit_templates
2927 && !flag_use_repository)
2928 || (flag_implicit_inline_templates
2929 && TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
2930 && DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl)))
2931 comdat_p = true;
2932 else
2933 /* If we are not implicitly generating templates, then mark
2934 this entity as undefined in this translation unit. */
2935 import_p = true;
2936 }
2937 else if (DECL_FUNCTION_MEMBER_P (decl))
2938 {
2939 if (!DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl))
2940 {
2941 tree ctype = DECL_CONTEXT (decl);
2942 import_export_class (ctype);
2943 if (CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_KNOWN (ctype))
2944 {
2945 DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (decl)
2946 = ! (CLASSTYPE_INTERFACE_ONLY (ctype)
2947 || (DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl)
2948 && ! flag_implement_inlines
2949 && !DECL_VINDEX (decl)));
2950
2951 if (!DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (decl))
2952 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 1;
2953
2954 /* Always make artificials weak. */
2955 if (DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl) && flag_weak)
2956 comdat_p = true;
2957 else
2958 maybe_make_one_only (decl);
2959 }
2960 }
2961 else
2962 comdat_p = true;
2963 }
2964 else
2965 comdat_p = true;
2966
2967 if (import_p)
2968 {
2969 /* If we are importing DECL into this translation unit, mark is
2970 an undefined here. */
2971 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 1;
2972 DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (decl) = 0;
2973 }
2974 else if (comdat_p)
2975 {
2976 /* If we decided to put DECL in COMDAT, mark it accordingly at
2977 this point. */
2978 comdat_linkage (decl);
2979 }
2980
2981 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (decl) = 1;
2982}

2984/* Return an expression that performs the destruction of DECL, which
2985 must be a VAR_DECL whose type has a non-trivial destructor, or is
2986 an array whose (innermost) elements have a non-trivial destructor. */
2987
2988tree
2989build_cleanup (tree decl)
2990{
2991 tree clean = cxx_maybe_build_cleanup (decl, tf_warning_or_error);
2992 gcc_assert (clean != NULL_TREE);
2993 return clean;
2994}

2996/* Returns the initialization guard variable for the variable DECL,
2997 which has static storage duration. */
2998
2999tree
3000get_guard (tree decl)
3001{
3002 tree sname;
3003 tree guard;
3004
3005 sname = mangle_guard_variable (decl);
3006 guard = IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (sname);
3007 if (! guard)
3008 {
3009 tree guard_type;
3010
3011 /* We use a type that is big enough to contain a mutex as well
3012 as an integer counter. */
3013 guard_type = targetm.cxx.guard_type ();
3014 guard = build_decl (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
3015 VAR_DECL, sname, guard_type);
3016
3017 /* The guard should have the same linkage as what it guards. */
3018 TREE_PUBLIC (guard) = TREE_PUBLIC (decl);
3019 TREE_STATIC (guard) = TREE_STATIC (decl);
3020 DECL_COMMON (guard) = DECL_COMMON (decl);
3021 DECL_COMDAT (guard) = DECL_COMDAT (decl);
3022 CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (guard) = CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (decl);
3023 set_decl_tls_model (guard, DECL_TLS_MODEL (decl));
3024 if (DECL_ONE_ONLY (decl))
3025 make_decl_one_only (guard, cxx_comdat_group (guard));
3026 if (TREE_PUBLIC (decl))
3027 DECL_WEAK (guard) = DECL_WEAK (decl);
3028 DECL_VISIBILITY (guard) = DECL_VISIBILITY (decl);
3029 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (guard) = DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (decl);
3030
3031 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (guard) = 1;
3032 DECL_IGNORED_P (guard) = 1;
3033 TREE_USED (guard) = 1;
3034 pushdecl_top_level_and_finish (guard, NULL_TREE);
3035 }
3036 return guard;
3037}
3038
3039/* Return an atomic load of src with the appropriate memory model. */
3040
3041static tree
3042build_atomic_load_byte (tree src, HOST_WIDE_INT model)
3043{
3044 tree ptr_type = build_pointer_type (char_type_node);
3045 tree mem_model = build_int_cst (integer_type_node, model);
3046 tree t, addr, val;
3047 unsigned int size;
3048 int fncode;
3049
3050 size = tree_to_uhwi (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (char_type_node));
3051
3052 fncode = BUILT_IN_ATOMIC_LOAD_N + exact_log2 (size) + 1;
3053 t = builtin_decl_implicit ((enum built_in_function) fncode);
3054
3055 addr = build1 (ADDR_EXPR, ptr_type, src);
3056 val = build_call_expr (t, 2, addr, mem_model);
3057 return val;
3058}
3059
3060/* Return those bits of the GUARD variable that should be set when the
3061 guarded entity is actually initialized. */
3062
3063static tree
3064get_guard_bits (tree guard)
3065{
3066 if (!targetm.cxx.guard_mask_bit ())
3067 {
3068 /* We only set the first byte of the guard, in order to leave room
3069 for a mutex in the high-order bits. */
3070 guard = build1 (ADDR_EXPR,
3071 build_pointer_type (TREE_TYPE (guard)),
3072 guard);
3073 guard = build1 (NOP_EXPR,
3074 build_pointer_type (char_type_node),
3075 guard);
3076 guard = build1 (INDIRECT_REF, char_type_node, guard);
3077 }
3078
3079 return guard;
3080}
3081
3082/* Return an expression which determines whether or not the GUARD
3083 variable has already been initialized. */
3084
3085tree
3086get_guard_cond (tree guard, bool thread_safe)
3087{
3088 tree guard_value;
3089
3090 if (!thread_safe)
3091 guard = get_guard_bits (guard);
3092 else
3093 guard = build_atomic_load_byte (guard, MEMMODEL_ACQUIRE);
3094
3095 /* Mask off all but the low bit. */
3096 if (targetm.cxx.guard_mask_bit ())
3097 {
3098 guard_value = integer_one_node;
3099 if (!same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (guard_value), TREE_TYPE (guard)))
3100 guard_value = fold_convert (TREE_TYPE (guard), guard_value);
3101 guard = cp_build_binary_op (input_location,
3102 BIT_AND_EXPR, guard, guard_value,
3103 tf_warning_or_error);
3104 }
3105
3106 guard_value = integer_zero_node;
3107 if (!same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (guard_value), TREE_TYPE (guard)))
3108 guard_value = fold_convert (TREE_TYPE (guard), guard_value);
3109 return cp_build_binary_op (input_location,
3110 EQ_EXPR, guard, guard_value,
3111 tf_warning_or_error);
3112}
3113
3114/* Return an expression which sets the GUARD variable, indicating that
3115 the variable being guarded has been initialized. */
3116
3117tree
3118set_guard (tree guard)
3119{
3120 tree guard_init;
3121
3122 /* Set the GUARD to one. */
3123 guard = get_guard_bits (guard);
3124 guard_init = integer_one_node;
3125 if (!same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (guard_init), TREE_TYPE (guard)))
3126 guard_init = fold_convert (TREE_TYPE (guard), guard_init);
3127 return cp_build_modify_expr (input_location, guard, NOP_EXPR, guard_init,
3128 tf_warning_or_error);
3129}

3131/* Returns true iff we can tell that VAR does not have a dynamic
3132 initializer. */
3133
3134static bool
3135var_defined_without_dynamic_init (tree var)
3136{
3137 /* If it's defined in another TU, we can't tell. */
3138 if (DECL_EXTERNAL (var))
3139 return false;
3140 /* If it has a non-trivial destructor, registering the destructor
3141 counts as dynamic initialization. */
3142 if (TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (TREE_TYPE (var)))
3143 return false;
3144 /* If it's in this TU, its initializer has been processed, unless
3145 it's a case of self-initialization, then DECL_INITIALIZED_P is
3146 false while the initializer is handled by finish_id_expression. */
3147 if (!DECL_INITIALIZED_P (var))
3148 return false;
3149 /* If it has no initializer or a constant one, it's not dynamic. */
3150 return (!DECL_NONTRIVIALLY_INITIALIZED_P (var)
3151 || DECL_INITIALIZED_BY_CONSTANT_EXPRESSION_P (var));
3152}
3153
3154/* Returns true iff VAR is a variable that needs uses to be
3155 wrapped for possible dynamic initialization. */
3156
3157static bool
3158var_needs_tls_wrapper (tree var)
3159{
3160 return (!error_operand_p (var)
3161 && CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (var)
3162 && !DECL_GNU_TLS_P (var)
3163 && !DECL_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (var)
3164 && !var_defined_without_dynamic_init (var));
3165}

3167/* Get the FUNCTION_DECL for the shared TLS init function for this
3168 translation unit. */
3169
3170static tree
3171get_local_tls_init_fn (void)
3172{
3173 tree sname = get_identifier ("__tls_init");
3174 tree fn = IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (sname);
3175 if (!fn)
3176 {
3177 fn = build_lang_decl (FUNCTION_DECL, sname,
3178 build_function_type (void_type_node,
3179 void_list_node));
3180 SET_DECL_LANGUAGE (fn, lang_c);
3181 TREE_PUBLIC (fn) = false;
3182 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (fn) = true;
3183 mark_used (fn);
3184 SET_IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (sname, fn);
3185 }

3187}
3188
3189/* Get a FUNCTION_DECL for the init function for the thread_local
3190 variable VAR. The init function will be an alias to the function
3191 that initializes all the non-local TLS variables in the translation
3192 unit. The init function is only used by the wrapper function. */
3193
3194static tree
3195get_tls_init_fn (tree var)
3196{
3197 /* Only C++11 TLS vars need this init fn. */
3198 if (!var_needs_tls_wrapper (var))
3199 return NULL_TREE;
3200
3201 /* If -fno-extern-tls-init, assume that we don't need to call
3202 a tls init function for a variable defined in another TU. */
3203 if (!flag_extern_tls_init && DECL_EXTERNAL (var))
3204 return NULL_TREE;
3205
3206#ifdef ASM_OUTPUT_DEF
3207 /* If the variable is internal, or if we can't generate aliases,
3208 call the local init function directly. */
3209 if (!TREE_PUBLIC (var))
3210#endif
3211 return get_local_tls_init_fn ();
3212
3213 tree sname = mangle_tls_init_fn (var);
3214 tree fn = IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (sname);
3215 if (!fn)
3216 {
3217 fn = build_lang_decl (FUNCTION_DECL, sname,
3218 build_function_type (void_type_node,
3219 void_list_node));
3220 SET_DECL_LANGUAGE (fn, lang_c);
3221 TREE_PUBLIC (fn) = TREE_PUBLIC (var);
3222 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (fn) = true;
3223 DECL_COMDAT (fn) = DECL_COMDAT (var);
3224 DECL_EXTERNAL (fn) = DECL_EXTERNAL (var);
3225 if (DECL_ONE_ONLY (var))
3226 make_decl_one_only (fn, cxx_comdat_group (fn));
3227 if (TREE_PUBLIC (var))
3228 {
3229 tree obtype = strip_array_types (non_reference (TREE_TYPE (var)));
3230 /* If the variable is defined somewhere else and might have static
3231 initialization, make the init function a weak reference. */
3232 if ((!TYPE_NEEDS_CONSTRUCTING (obtype)
3233 || TYPE_HAS_CONSTEXPR_CTOR (obtype))
3234 && TYPE_HAS_TRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (obtype)
3235 && DECL_EXTERNAL (var))
3236 declare_weak (fn);
3237 else
3238 DECL_WEAK (fn) = DECL_WEAK (var);
3239 }
3240 DECL_VISIBILITY (fn) = DECL_VISIBILITY (var);
3241 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (fn) = DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (var);
3242 DECL_DLLIMPORT_P (fn) = DECL_DLLIMPORT_P (var);
3243 DECL_IGNORED_P (fn) = 1;
3244 mark_used (fn);
3245
3246 DECL_BEFRIENDING_CLASSES (fn) = var;
3247
3248 SET_IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (sname, fn);
3249 }
3250 return fn;
3251}
3252
3253/* Get a FUNCTION_DECL for the init wrapper function for the thread_local
3254 variable VAR. The wrapper function calls the init function (if any) for
3255 VAR and then returns a reference to VAR. The wrapper function is used
3256 in place of VAR everywhere VAR is mentioned. */
3257
3258tree
3259get_tls_wrapper_fn (tree var)
3260{
3261 /* Only C++11 TLS vars need this wrapper fn. */
3262 if (!var_needs_tls_wrapper (var))
3263 return NULL_TREE;
3264
3265 tree sname = mangle_tls_wrapper_fn (var);
3266 tree fn = IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (sname);
3267 if (!fn)
3268 {
3269 /* A named rvalue reference is an lvalue, so the wrapper should
3270 always return an lvalue reference. */
3271 tree type = non_reference (TREE_TYPE (var));
3272 type = build_reference_type (type);
3273 tree fntype = build_function_type (type, void_list_node);
3274 fn = build_lang_decl (FUNCTION_DECL, sname, fntype);
3275 SET_DECL_LANGUAGE (fn, lang_c);
3276 TREE_PUBLIC (fn) = TREE_PUBLIC (var);
3277 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (fn) = true;
3278 DECL_IGNORED_P (fn) = 1;
3279 /* The wrapper is inline and emitted everywhere var is used. */
3280 DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (fn) = true;
3281 if (TREE_PUBLIC (var))
3282 {
3283 comdat_linkage (fn);
3284#ifdef HAVE_GAS_HIDDEN
3285 /* Make the wrapper bind locally; there's no reason to share
3286 the wrapper between multiple shared objects. */
3287 DECL_VISIBILITY (fn) = VISIBILITY_INTERNAL;
3288 DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED (fn) = true;
3289#endif
3290 }
3291 if (!TREE_PUBLIC (fn))
3292 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN (fn) = true;
3293 mark_used (fn);
3294 note_vague_linkage_fn (fn);
3295
3296#if 0
3297 /* We want CSE to commonize calls to the wrapper, but marking it as
3298 pure is unsafe since it has side-effects. I guess we need a new
3299 ECF flag even weaker than ECF_PURE. FIXME! */
3300 DECL_PURE_P (fn) = true;
3301#endif
3302
3303 DECL_BEFRIENDING_CLASSES (fn) = var;
3304
3305 SET_IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (sname, fn);
3306 }
3307 return fn;
3308}
3309
3310/* At EOF, generate the definition for the TLS wrapper function FN:
3311
3312 T& var_wrapper() {
3313 if (init_fn) init_fn();
3314 return var;
3315 } */
3316
3317static void
3318generate_tls_wrapper (tree fn)
3319{
3320 tree var = DECL_BEFRIENDING_CLASSES (fn);
3321
3322 start_preparsed_function (fn, NULL_TREE, SF_DEFAULT | SF_PRE_PARSED);
3323 tree body = begin_function_body ();
3324 /* Only call the init fn if there might be one. */
3325 if (tree init_fn = get_tls_init_fn (var))
3326 {
3327 tree if_stmt = NULL_TREE;
3328 /* If init_fn is a weakref, make sure it exists before calling. */
3329 if (lookup_attribute ("weak", DECL_ATTRIBUTES (init_fn)))
3330 {
3331 if_stmt = begin_if_stmt ();
3332 tree addr = cp_build_addr_expr (init_fn, tf_warning_or_error);
3333 tree cond = cp_build_binary_op (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (var),
3334 NE_EXPR, addr, nullptr_node,
3335 tf_warning_or_error);
3336 finish_if_stmt_cond (cond, if_stmt);
3337 }
3338 finish_expr_stmt (build_cxx_call
3339 (init_fn, 0, NULL, tf_warning_or_error));
3340 if (if_stmt)
3341 {
3342 finish_then_clause (if_stmt);
3343 finish_if_stmt (if_stmt);
3344 }
3345 }
3346 else
3347 /* If there's no initialization, the wrapper is a constant function. */
3348 TREE_READONLY (fn) = true;
3349 finish_return_stmt (convert_from_reference (var));
3350 finish_function_body (body);
3351 expand_or_defer_fn (finish_function (0));
3352}

3354/* Start the process of running a particular set of global constructors
3355 or destructors. Subroutine of do_[cd]tors. Also called from
3356 vtv_start_verification_constructor_init_function. */
3357
3358static tree
3359start_objects (int method_type, int initp)
3360{
3361 tree body;
3362 tree fndecl;
3363 char type[14];
3364
3365 /* Make ctor or dtor function. METHOD_TYPE may be 'I' or 'D'. */
3366
3367 if (initp != DEFAULT_INIT_PRIORITY)
3368 {
3369 char joiner;
3370
3371#ifdef JOINER
3372 joiner = JOINER;
3373#else
3374 joiner = '_';
3375#endif
3376
3377 sprintf (type, "sub_%c%c%.5u", method_type, joiner, initp);
3378 }
3379 else
3380 sprintf (type, "sub_%c", method_type);
3381
3382 fndecl = build_lang_decl (FUNCTION_DECL,
3383 get_file_function_name (type),
3384 build_function_type_list (void_type_node,
3385 NULL_TREE));
3386 start_preparsed_function (fndecl, /*attrs=*/NULL_TREE, SF_PRE_PARSED);
3387
3388 TREE_PUBLIC (current_function_decl) = 0;
3389
3390 /* Mark as artificial because it's not explicitly in the user's
3391 source code. */
3392 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (current_function_decl) = 1;
3393
3394 /* Mark this declaration as used to avoid spurious warnings. */
3395 TREE_USED (current_function_decl) = 1;
3396
3397 /* Mark this function as a global constructor or destructor. */
3398 if (method_type == 'I')
3399 DECL_GLOBAL_CTOR_P (current_function_decl) = 1;
3400 else
3401 DECL_GLOBAL_DTOR_P (current_function_decl) = 1;
3402
3403 body = begin_compound_stmt (BCS_FN_BODY);
3404
3405 return body;
3406}

3408/* Finish the process of running a particular set of global constructors
3409 or destructors. Subroutine of do_[cd]tors. */

3434/* The names of the parameters to the function created to handle
3435 initializations and destructions for objects with static storage
3436 duration. */
3437#define INITIALIZE_P_IDENTIFIER "__initialize_p"
3438#define PRIORITY_IDENTIFIER "__priority"
3439
3440/* The name of the function we create to handle initializations and
3441 destructions for objects with static storage duration. */
3442#define SSDF_IDENTIFIER "__static_initialization_and_destruction"
3443
3444/* The declaration for the __INITIALIZE_P argument. */
3445static GTY(()) tree initialize_p_decl;
3446
3447/* The declaration for the __PRIORITY argument. */
3448static GTY(()) tree priority_decl;
3449
3450/* The declaration for the static storage duration function. */
3451static GTY(()) tree ssdf_decl;
3452
3453/* All the static storage duration functions created in this
3454 translation unit. */
3455static GTY(()) vec<tree, va_gc> *ssdf_decls;
3456
3457/* A map from priority levels to information about that priority
3458 level. There may be many such levels, so efficient lookup is
3459 important. */
3460static splay_tree priority_info_map;
3461
3462/* Begins the generation of the function that will handle all
3463 initialization and destruction of objects with static storage
3464 duration. The function generated takes two parameters of type
3465 `int': __INITIALIZE_P and __PRIORITY. If __INITIALIZE_P is
3466 nonzero, it performs initializations. Otherwise, it performs
3467 destructions. It only performs those initializations or
3468 destructions with the indicated __PRIORITY. The generated function
3469 returns no value.
3470
3471 It is assumed that this function will only be called once per
3472 translation unit. */
3473
3474static tree
3475start_static_storage_duration_function (unsigned count)
3476{
3477 tree type;
3478 tree body;
3479 char id[sizeof (SSDF_IDENTIFIER) + 1 /* '\0' */ + 32];
3480
3481 /* Create the identifier for this function. It will be of the form
3482 SSDF_IDENTIFIER_<number>. */
3483 sprintf (id, "%s_%u", SSDF_IDENTIFIER, count);
3484
3485 type = build_function_type_list (void_type_node,
3486 integer_type_node, integer_type_node,
3487 NULL_TREE);
3488
3489 /* Create the FUNCTION_DECL itself. */
3490 ssdf_decl = build_lang_decl (FUNCTION_DECL,
3491 get_identifier (id),
3492 type);
3493 TREE_PUBLIC (ssdf_decl) = 0;
3494 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (ssdf_decl) = 1;
3495
3496 /* Put this function in the list of functions to be called from the
3497 static constructors and destructors. */
3498 if (!ssdf_decls)
3499 {
3500 vec_alloc (ssdf_decls, 32);
3501
3502 /* Take this opportunity to initialize the map from priority
3503 numbers to information about that priority level. */
3504 priority_info_map = splay_tree_new (splay_tree_compare_ints,
3505 /*delete_key_fn=*/0,
3506 /*delete_value_fn=*/
3507 (splay_tree_delete_value_fn) &free);
3508
3509 /* We always need to generate functions for the
3510 DEFAULT_INIT_PRIORITY so enter it now. That way when we walk
3511 priorities later, we'll be sure to find the
3512 DEFAULT_INIT_PRIORITY. */
3513 get_priority_info (DEFAULT_INIT_PRIORITY);
3514 }
3515
3516 vec_safe_push (ssdf_decls, ssdf_decl);
3517
3518 /* Create the argument list. */
3519 initialize_p_decl = cp_build_parm_decl
3520 (get_identifier (INITIALIZE_P_IDENTIFIER), integer_type_node);
3521 DECL_CONTEXT (initialize_p_decl) = ssdf_decl;
3522 TREE_USED (initialize_p_decl) = 1;
3523 priority_decl = cp_build_parm_decl
3524 (get_identifier (PRIORITY_IDENTIFIER), integer_type_node);
3525 DECL_CONTEXT (priority_decl) = ssdf_decl;
3526 TREE_USED (priority_decl) = 1;
3527
3528 DECL_CHAIN (initialize_p_decl) = priority_decl;
3529 DECL_ARGUMENTS (ssdf_decl) = initialize_p_decl;
3530
3531 /* Put the function in the global scope. */
3532 pushdecl (ssdf_decl);
3533
3534 /* Start the function itself. This is equivalent to declaring the
3535 function as:
3536
3537 static void __ssdf (int __initialize_p, init __priority_p);
3538
3539 It is static because we only need to call this function from the
3540 various constructor and destructor functions for this module. */
3541 start_preparsed_function (ssdf_decl,
3542 /*attrs=*/NULL_TREE,
3543 SF_PRE_PARSED);
3544
3545 /* Set up the scope of the outermost block in the function. */
3546 body = begin_compound_stmt (BCS_FN_BODY);
3547
3548 return body;
3549}

3551/* Finish the generation of the function which performs initialization
3552 and destruction of objects with static storage duration. After
3553 this point, no more such objects can be created. */
3554
3555static void
3556finish_static_storage_duration_function (tree body)
3557{
3558 /* Close out the function. */
3559 finish_compound_stmt (body);
3560 expand_or_defer_fn (finish_function (0));
3561}

3563/* Return the information about the indicated PRIORITY level. If no
3564 code to handle this level has yet been generated, generate the
3565 appropriate prologue. */
3566
3567static priority_info
3568get_priority_info (int priority)
3569{
3570 priority_info pi;
3571 splay_tree_node n;
3572
3573 n = splay_tree_lookup (priority_info_map,
3574 (splay_tree_key) priority);
3575 if (!n)
3576 {
3577 /* Create a new priority information structure, and insert it
3578 into the map. */
3579 pi = XNEW (struct priority_info_s);
3580 pi->initializations_p = 0;
3581 pi->destructions_p = 0;
3582 splay_tree_insert (priority_info_map,
3583 (splay_tree_key) priority,
3584 (splay_tree_value) pi);
3585 }
3586 else
3587 pi = (priority_info) n->value;
3588
3589 return pi;
3590}

3592/* The effective initialization priority of a DECL. */
3593
3594#define DECL_EFFECTIVE_INIT_PRIORITY(decl) \
3595 ((!DECL_HAS_INIT_PRIORITY_P (decl) || DECL_INIT_PRIORITY (decl) == 0) \
3596 ? DEFAULT_INIT_PRIORITY : DECL_INIT_PRIORITY (decl))
3597
3598/* Whether a DECL needs a guard to protect it against multiple
3599 initialization. */
3600
3601#define NEEDS_GUARD_P(decl) (TREE_PUBLIC (decl) && (DECL_COMMON (decl) \
3602 || DECL_ONE_ONLY (decl) \
3603 || DECL_WEAK (decl)))
3604
3605/* Called from one_static_initialization_or_destruction(),
3606 via walk_tree.
3607 Walks the initializer list of a global variable and looks for
3608 temporary variables (DECL_NAME() == NULL and DECL_ARTIFICIAL != 0)
3609 and that have their DECL_CONTEXT() == NULL.
3610 For each such temporary variable, set their DECL_CONTEXT() to
3611 the current function. This is necessary because otherwise
3612 some optimizers (enabled by -O2 -fprofile-arcs) might crash
3613 when trying to refer to a temporary variable that does not have
3614 it's DECL_CONTECT() properly set. */
3615static tree
3616fix_temporary_vars_context_r (tree *node,
3617 int * /*unused*/,
3618 void * /*unused1*/)
3619{
3620 gcc_assert (current_function_decl);
3621
3622 if (TREE_CODE (*node) == BIND_EXPR)
3623 {
3624 tree var;
3625
3626 for (var = BIND_EXPR_VARS (*node); var; var = DECL_CHAIN (var))
3627 if (VAR_P (var)
3628 && !DECL_NAME (var)
3629 && DECL_ARTIFICIAL (var)
3630 && !DECL_CONTEXT (var))
3631 DECL_CONTEXT (var) = current_function_decl;
3632 }
3633
3634 return NULL_TREE;
3635}
3636
3637/* Set up to handle the initialization or destruction of DECL. If
3638 INITP is nonzero, we are initializing the variable. Otherwise, we
3639 are destroying it. */
3640
3641static void
3642one_static_initialization_or_destruction (tree decl, tree init, bool initp)
3643{
3644 tree guard_if_stmt = NULL_TREE;
3645 tree guard;
3646
3647 /* If we are supposed to destruct and there's a trivial destructor,
3648 nothing has to be done. */
3649 if (!initp
3650 && TYPE_HAS_TRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
3651 return;
3652
3653 /* Trick the compiler into thinking we are at the file and line
3654 where DECL was declared so that error-messages make sense, and so
3655 that the debugger will show somewhat sensible file and line
3656 information. */
3657 input_location = DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl);
3658
3659 /* Make sure temporary variables in the initialiser all have
3660 their DECL_CONTEXT() set to a value different from NULL_TREE.
3661 This can happen when global variables initializers are built.
3662 In that case, the DECL_CONTEXT() of the global variables _AND_ of all
3663 the temporary variables that might have been generated in the
3664 accompanying initializers is NULL_TREE, meaning the variables have been
3665 declared in the global namespace.
3666 What we want to do here is to fix that and make sure the DECL_CONTEXT()
3667 of the temporaries are set to the current function decl. */
3668 cp_walk_tree_without_duplicates (&init,
3669 fix_temporary_vars_context_r,
3670 NULL);
3671
3672 /* Because of:
3673
3674 [class.access.spec]
3675
3676 Access control for implicit calls to the constructors,
3677 the conversion functions, or the destructor called to
3678 create and destroy a static data member is performed as
3679 if these calls appeared in the scope of the member's
3680 class.
3681
3682 we pretend we are in a static member function of the class of
3683 which the DECL is a member. */
3684 if (member_p (decl))
3685 {
3686 DECL_CONTEXT (current_function_decl) = DECL_CONTEXT (decl);
3687 DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (current_function_decl) = 1;
3688 }
3689
3690 /* Assume we don't need a guard. */
3691 guard = NULL_TREE;
3692 /* We need a guard if this is an object with external linkage that
3693 might be initialized in more than one place. (For example, a
3694 static data member of a template, when the data member requires
3695 construction.) */
3696 if (NEEDS_GUARD_P (decl))
3697 {
3698 tree guard_cond;
3699
3700 guard = get_guard (decl);
3701
3702 /* When using __cxa_atexit, we just check the GUARD as we would
3703 for a local static. */
3704 if (flag_use_cxa_atexit)
3705 {
3706 /* When using __cxa_atexit, we never try to destroy
3707 anything from a static destructor. */
3708 gcc_assert (initp);
3709 guard_cond = get_guard_cond (guard, false);
3710 }
3711 /* If we don't have __cxa_atexit, then we will be running
3712 destructors from .fini sections, or their equivalents. So,
3713 we need to know how many times we've tried to initialize this
3714 object. We do initializations only if the GUARD is zero,
3715 i.e., if we are the first to initialize the variable. We do
3716 destructions only if the GUARD is one, i.e., if we are the
3717 last to destroy the variable. */
3718 else if (initp)
3719 guard_cond
3720 = cp_build_binary_op (input_location,
3721 EQ_EXPR,
3722 cp_build_unary_op (PREINCREMENT_EXPR,
3723 guard,
3724 /*noconvert=*/true,
3725 tf_warning_or_error),
3726 integer_one_node,
3727 tf_warning_or_error);
3728 else
3729 guard_cond
3730 = cp_build_binary_op (input_location,
3731 EQ_EXPR,
3732 cp_build_unary_op (PREDECREMENT_EXPR,
3733 guard,
3734 /*noconvert=*/true,
3735 tf_warning_or_error),
3736 integer_zero_node,
3737 tf_warning_or_error);
3738
3739 guard_if_stmt = begin_if_stmt ();
3740 finish_if_stmt_cond (guard_cond, guard_if_stmt);
3741 }
3742
3743
3744 /* If we're using __cxa_atexit, we have not already set the GUARD,
3745 so we must do so now. */
3746 if (guard && initp && flag_use_cxa_atexit)
3747 finish_expr_stmt (set_guard (guard));
3748
3749 /* Perform the initialization or destruction. */
3750 if (initp)
3751 {
3752 if (init)
3753 {
3754 finish_expr_stmt (init);
3755 if (flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_ADDRESS)
3756 {
3757 varpool_node *vnode = varpool_node::get (decl);
3758 if (vnode)
3759 vnode->dynamically_initialized = 1;
3760 }
3761 }
3762
3763 /* If we're using __cxa_atexit, register a function that calls the
3764 destructor for the object. */
3765 if (flag_use_cxa_atexit)
3766 finish_expr_stmt (register_dtor_fn (decl));
3767 }
3768 else
3769 finish_expr_stmt (build_cleanup (decl));
3770
3771 /* Finish the guard if-stmt, if necessary. */
3772 if (guard)
3773 {
3774 finish_then_clause (guard_if_stmt);
3775 finish_if_stmt (guard_if_stmt);
3776 }
3777
3778 /* Now that we're done with DECL we don't need to pretend to be a
3779 member of its class any longer. */
3780 DECL_CONTEXT (current_function_decl) = NULL_TREE;
3781 DECL_STATIC_FUNCTION_P (current_function_decl) = 0;
3782}
3783
3784/* Generate code to do the initialization or destruction of the decls in VARS,
3785 a TREE_LIST of VAR_DECL with static storage duration.
3786 Whether initialization or destruction is performed is specified by INITP. */
3787
3788static void
3789do_static_initialization_or_destruction (tree vars, bool initp)
3790{
3791 tree node, init_if_stmt, cond;
3792
3793 /* Build the outer if-stmt to check for initialization or destruction. */
3794 init_if_stmt = begin_if_stmt ();
3795 cond = initp ? integer_one_node : integer_zero_node;
3796 cond = cp_build_binary_op (input_location,
3797 EQ_EXPR,
3798 initialize_p_decl,
3799 cond,
3800 tf_warning_or_error);
3801 finish_if_stmt_cond (cond, init_if_stmt);
3802
3803 /* To make sure dynamic construction doesn't access globals from other
3804 compilation units where they might not be yet constructed, for
3805 -fsanitize=address insert __asan_before_dynamic_init call that
3806 prevents access to either all global variables that need construction
3807 in other compilation units, or at least those that haven't been
3808 initialized yet. Variables that need dynamic construction in
3809 the current compilation unit are kept accessible. */
3810 if (initp && (flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_ADDRESS))
3811 finish_expr_stmt (asan_dynamic_init_call (/*after_p=*/false));
3812
3813 node = vars;
3814 do {
3815 tree decl = TREE_VALUE (node);
3816 tree priority_if_stmt;
3817 int priority;
3818 priority_info pi;
3819
3820 /* If we don't need a destructor, there's nothing to do. Avoid
3821 creating a possibly empty if-stmt. */
3822 if (!initp && TYPE_HAS_TRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
3823 {
3824 node = TREE_CHAIN (node);
3825 continue;
3826 }
3827
3828 /* Remember that we had an initialization or finalization at this
3829 priority. */
3830 priority = DECL_EFFECTIVE_INIT_PRIORITY (decl);
3831 pi = get_priority_info (priority);
3832 if (initp)
3833 pi->initializations_p = 1;
3834 else
3835 pi->destructions_p = 1;
3836
3837 /* Conditionalize this initialization on being in the right priority
3838 and being initializing/finalizing appropriately. */
3839 priority_if_stmt = begin_if_stmt ();
3840 cond = cp_build_binary_op (input_location,
3841 EQ_EXPR,
3842 priority_decl,
3843 build_int_cst (NULL_TREE, priority),
3844 tf_warning_or_error);
3845 finish_if_stmt_cond (cond, priority_if_stmt);
3846
3847 /* Process initializers with same priority. */
3848 for (; node
3849 && DECL_EFFECTIVE_INIT_PRIORITY (TREE_VALUE (node)) == priority;
3850 node = TREE_CHAIN (node))
3851 /* Do one initialization or destruction. */
3852 one_static_initialization_or_destruction (TREE_VALUE (node),
3853 TREE_PURPOSE (node), initp);
3854
3855 /* Finish up the priority if-stmt body. */
3856 finish_then_clause (priority_if_stmt);
3857 finish_if_stmt (priority_if_stmt);
3858
3859 } while (node);
3860
3861 /* Revert what __asan_before_dynamic_init did by calling
3862 __asan_after_dynamic_init. */
3863 if (initp && (flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_ADDRESS))
3864 finish_expr_stmt (asan_dynamic_init_call (/*after_p=*/true));
3865
3866 /* Finish up the init/destruct if-stmt body. */
3867 finish_then_clause (init_if_stmt);
3868 finish_if_stmt (init_if_stmt);
3869}
3870
3871/* VARS is a list of variables with static storage duration which may
3872 need initialization and/or finalization. Remove those variables
3873 that don't really need to be initialized or finalized, and return
3874 the resulting list. The order in which the variables appear in
3875 VARS is in reverse order of the order in which they should actually
3876 be initialized. The list we return is in the unreversed order;
3877 i.e., the first variable should be initialized first. */
3878
3879static tree
3880prune_vars_needing_no_initialization (tree *vars)
3881{
3882 tree *var = vars;
3883 tree result = NULL_TREE;
3884
3885 while (*var)
3886 {
3887 tree t = *var;
3888 tree decl = TREE_VALUE (t);
3889 tree init = TREE_PURPOSE (t);
3890
3891 /* Deal gracefully with error. */
3892 if (error_operand_p (decl))
3893 {
3894 var = &TREE_CHAIN (t);
3895 continue;
3896 }
3897
3898 /* The only things that can be initialized are variables. */
3899 gcc_assert (VAR_P (decl));
3900
3901 /* If this object is not defined, we don't need to do anything
3902 here. */
3903 if (DECL_EXTERNAL (decl))
3904 {
3905 var = &TREE_CHAIN (t);
3906 continue;
3907 }
3908
3909 /* Also, if the initializer already contains errors, we can bail
3910 out now. */
3911 if (init && TREE_CODE (init) == TREE_LIST
3912 && value_member (error_mark_node, init))
3913 {
3914 var = &TREE_CHAIN (t);
3915 continue;
3916 }
3917
3918 /* This variable is going to need initialization and/or
3919 finalization, so we add it to the list. */
3920 *var = TREE_CHAIN (t);
3921 TREE_CHAIN (t) = result;
3922 result = t;
3923 }
3924
3925 return result;
3926}

3929 VARS. */
3930
3931static void
3932write_out_vars (tree vars)
3933{
3934 tree v;
3935
3936 for (v = vars; v; v = TREE_CHAIN (v))

3943 }
3944 }
3945}

3947/* Generate a static constructor (if CONSTRUCTOR_P) or destructor
3948 (otherwise) that will initialize all global objects with static
3949 storage duration having the indicated PRIORITY. */
3950
3951static void
3952generate_ctor_or_dtor_function (bool constructor_p, int priority,
3953 location_t *locus)
3954{
3955 char function_key;
3956 tree fndecl;
3957 tree body;
3958 size_t i;
3959
3960 input_location = *locus;
3961 /* ??? */
3962 /* Was: locus->line++; */
3963
3964 /* We use `I' to indicate initialization and `D' to indicate
3965 destruction. */
3966 function_key = constructor_p ? 'I' : 'D';
3967
3968 /* We emit the function lazily, to avoid generating empty
3969 global constructors and destructors. */
3970 body = NULL_TREE;
3971
3972 /* For Objective-C++, we may need to initialize metadata found in this module.
3973 This must be done _before_ any other static initializations. */
3974 if (c_dialect_objc () && (priority == DEFAULT_INIT_PRIORITY)
3975 && constructor_p && objc_static_init_needed_p ())
3976 {
3977 body = start_objects (function_key, priority);
3978 objc_generate_static_init_call (NULL_TREE);
3979 }
3980
3981 /* Call the static storage duration function with appropriate
3982 arguments. */
3983 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (ssdf_decls, i, fndecl)
3984 {
3985 /* Calls to pure or const functions will expand to nothing. */
3986 if (! (flags_from_decl_or_type (fndecl) & (ECF_CONST | ECF_PURE)))
3987 {
3988 tree call;
3989
3990 if (! body)
3991 body = start_objects (function_key, priority);
3992
3993 call = cp_build_function_call_nary (fndecl, tf_warning_or_error,
3994 build_int_cst (NULL_TREE,
3995 constructor_p),
3996 build_int_cst (NULL_TREE,
3997 priority),
3998 NULL_TREE);
3999 finish_expr_stmt (call);
4000 }
4001 }
4002
4003 /* Close out the function. */
4004 if (body)
4005 finish_objects (function_key, priority, body);
4006}
4007
4008/* Generate constructor and destructor functions for the priority
4009 indicated by N. */
4010
4011static int
4012generate_ctor_and_dtor_functions_for_priority (splay_tree_node n, void * data)
4013{
4014 location_t *locus = (location_t *) data;
4015 int priority = (int) n->key;
4016 priority_info pi = (priority_info) n->value;
4017
4018 /* Generate the functions themselves, but only if they are really
4019 needed. */
4020 if (pi->initializations_p)
4021 generate_ctor_or_dtor_function (/*constructor_p=*/true, priority, locus);
4022 if (pi->destructions_p)
4023 generate_ctor_or_dtor_function (/*constructor_p=*/false, priority, locus);
4024
4025 /* Keep iterating. */
4026 return 0;
4027}
4028
4029/* Return C++ property of T, based on given operation OP. */
4030
4031static int
4032cpp_check (tree t, cpp_operation op)
4033{
4034 switch (op)
4035 {
4036 case HAS_DEPENDENT_TEMPLATE_ARGS:
4037 {
4038 tree ti = CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (t);
4039 if (!ti)
4040 return 0;
4041 ++processing_template_decl;
4042 const bool dep = any_dependent_template_arguments_p (TI_ARGS (ti));
4043 --processing_template_decl;
4044 return dep;
4045 }
4046 case IS_ABSTRACT:
4047 return DECL_PURE_VIRTUAL_P (t);
4048 case IS_CONSTRUCTOR:
4049 return DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (t);
4050 case IS_DESTRUCTOR:
4051 return DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (t);
4052 case IS_COPY_CONSTRUCTOR:
4053 return DECL_COPY_CONSTRUCTOR_P (t);
4054 case IS_MOVE_CONSTRUCTOR:
4055 return DECL_MOVE_CONSTRUCTOR_P (t);
4056 case IS_TEMPLATE:
4057 return TREE_CODE (t) == TEMPLATE_DECL;
4058 case IS_TRIVIAL:
4059 return trivial_type_p (t);
4060 default:
4061 return 0;
4062 }
4063}

4065/* Collect source file references recursively, starting from NAMESPC. */
4066
4067static void
4068collect_source_refs (tree namespc)
4069{
4070 tree t;
4071
4072 if (!namespc)
4073 return;
4074
4075 /* Iterate over names in this name space. */
4076 for (t = NAMESPACE_LEVEL (namespc)->names; t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
4077 if (!DECL_IS_BUILTIN (t) )
4078 collect_source_ref (DECL_SOURCE_FILE (t));
4079
4080 /* Dump siblings, if any */
4081 collect_source_refs (TREE_CHAIN (namespc));
4082
4083 /* Dump children, if any */
4084 collect_source_refs (NAMESPACE_LEVEL (namespc)->namespaces);
4085}

4087/* Collect decls relevant to SOURCE_FILE from all namespaces recursively,
4088 starting from NAMESPC. */
4089
4090static void
4091collect_ada_namespace (tree namespc, const char *source_file)
4092{
4093 if (!namespc)
4094 return;
4095

4097 collect_ada_nodes (NAMESPACE_LEVEL (namespc)->names, source_file);
4098
4099 /* Collect siblings, if any */
4100 collect_ada_namespace (TREE_CHAIN (namespc), source_file);
4101
4102 /* Collect children, if any */
4103 collect_ada_namespace (NAMESPACE_LEVEL (namespc)->namespaces, source_file);
4104}

4106/* Returns true iff there is a definition available for variable or
4107 function DECL. */
4108
4109bool
4110decl_defined_p (tree decl)
4111{
4112 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
4113 return (DECL_INITIAL (decl) != NULL_TREE
4114 /* A pending instantiation of a friend temploid is defined. */
4115 || (DECL_FRIEND_PSEUDO_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATION (decl)
4116 && DECL_INITIAL (DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT
4117 (DECL_TI_TEMPLATE (decl)))));
4118 else
4119 {
4120 gcc_assert (VAR_P (decl));
4121 return !DECL_EXTERNAL (decl);
4122 }
4123}
4124
4125/* Nonzero for a VAR_DECL whose value can be used in a constant expression.
4126
4127 [expr.const]
4128
4129 An integral constant-expression can only involve ... const
4130 variables of integral or enumeration types initialized with
4131 constant expressions ...
4132
4133 C++0x also allows constexpr variables and temporaries initialized
4134 with constant expressions. We handle the former here, but the latter
4135 are just folded away in cxx_eval_constant_expression.
4136
4137 The standard does not require that the expression be non-volatile.
4138 G++ implements the proposed correction in DR 457. */
4139
4140bool
4141decl_constant_var_p (tree decl)
4142{
4143 if (!decl_maybe_constant_var_p (decl))
4144 return false;
4145
4146 /* We don't know if a template static data member is initialized with
4147 a constant expression until we instantiate its initializer. Even
4148 in the case of a constexpr variable, we can't treat it as a
4149 constant until its initializer is complete in case it's used in
4150 its own initializer. */
4151 maybe_instantiate_decl (decl);
4152 return DECL_INITIALIZED_BY_CONSTANT_EXPRESSION_P (decl);
4153}
4154
4155/* Returns true if DECL could be a symbolic constant variable, depending on
4156 its initializer. */
4157
4158bool
4159decl_maybe_constant_var_p (tree decl)
4160{
4161 tree type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
4162 if (!VAR_P (decl))
4163 return false;
4164 if (DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (decl))
4165 return true;
4166 if (DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (decl))
4167 /* A proxy isn't constant. */
4168 return false;
4169 if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
4170 /* References can be constant. */
4171 return true;
4172 return (CP_TYPE_CONST_NON_VOLATILE_P (type)
4173 && INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (type));
4174}
4175
4176/* Complain that DECL uses a type with no linkage. In C++98 mode this is
4177 called from grokfndecl and grokvardecl; in all modes it is called from
4178 cp_write_global_declarations. */
4179
4180void
4181no_linkage_error (tree decl)
4182{
4183 if (cxx_dialect >= cxx11 && decl_defined_p (decl))
4184 /* In C++11 it's ok if the decl is defined. */
4185 return;
4186 tree t = no_linkage_check (TREE_TYPE (decl), /*relaxed_p=*/false);
4187 if (t == NULL_TREE)
4188 /* The type that got us on no_linkage_decls must have gotten a name for
4189 linkage purposes. */;
4190 else if (CLASS_TYPE_P (t) && TYPE_BEING_DEFINED (t))
4191 /* The type might end up having a typedef name for linkage purposes. */
4192 vec_safe_push (no_linkage_decls, decl);
4193 else if (TYPE_UNNAMED_P (t))
4194 {
4195 bool d = false;
4196 if (cxx_dialect >= cxx11)
4197 d = permerror (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), "%q#D, declared using "
4198 "unnamed type, is used but never defined", decl);
4199 else if (DECL_EXTERN_C_P (decl))
4200 /* Allow this; it's pretty common in C. */;
4201 else if (VAR_P (decl))
4202 /* DRs 132, 319 and 389 seem to indicate types with
4203 no linkage can only be used to declare extern "C"
4204 entities. Since it's not always an error in the
4205 ISO C++ 90 Standard, we only issue a warning. */
4206 d = warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), 0, "unnamed type "
4207 "with no linkage used to declare variable %q#D with "
4208 "linkage", decl);
4209 else
4210 d = permerror (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), "unnamed type with no "
4211 "linkage used to declare function %q#D with linkage",
4212 decl);
4213 if (d && is_typedef_decl (TYPE_NAME (t)))
4214 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (TYPE_NAME (t)), "%q#D does not refer "
4215 "to the unqualified type, so it is not used for linkage",
4216 TYPE_NAME (t));
4217 }
4218 else if (cxx_dialect >= cxx11)
4219 {
4220 if (VAR_P (decl) || !DECL_PURE_VIRTUAL_P (decl))
4221 permerror (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl),
4222 "%q#D, declared using local type "
4223 "%qT, is used but never defined", decl, t);
4224 }
4225 else if (VAR_P (decl))
4226 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), 0, "type %qT with no linkage "
4227 "used to declare variable %q#D with linkage", t, decl);
4228 else
4229 permerror (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), "type %qT with no linkage used "
4230 "to declare function %q#D with linkage", t, decl);
4231}

4238 collect_ada_namespace (global_namespace, source_file);
4239}

4250/* Build up the function to run dynamic initializers for thread_local
4251 variables in this translation unit and alias the init functions for the
4252 individual variables to it. */
4253
4254static void
4255handle_tls_init (void)
4256{
4257 tree vars = prune_vars_needing_no_initialization (&tls_aggregates);
4258 if (vars == NULL_TREE)
4259 return;
4260
4261 location_t loc = DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (TREE_VALUE (vars));
4262
4263 write_out_vars (vars);
4264
4265 tree guard = build_decl (loc, VAR_DECL, get_identifier ("__tls_guard"),
4266 boolean_type_node);
4267 TREE_PUBLIC (guard) = false;
4268 TREE_STATIC (guard) = true;
4269 DECL_ARTIFICIAL (guard) = true;
4270 DECL_IGNORED_P (guard) = true;
4271 TREE_USED (guard) = true;
4272 CP_DECL_THREAD_LOCAL_P (guard) = true;
4273 set_decl_tls_model (guard, decl_default_tls_model (guard));
4274 pushdecl_top_level_and_finish (guard, NULL_TREE);
4275
4276 tree fn = get_local_tls_init_fn ();
4277 start_preparsed_function (fn, NULL_TREE, SF_PRE_PARSED);
4278 tree body = begin_function_body ();
4279 tree if_stmt = begin_if_stmt ();
4280 tree cond = cp_build_unary_op (TRUTH_NOT_EXPR, guard, false,
4281 tf_warning_or_error);
4282 finish_if_stmt_cond (cond, if_stmt);
4283 finish_expr_stmt (cp_build_modify_expr (loc, guard, NOP_EXPR,
4284 boolean_true_node,
4285 tf_warning_or_error));
4286 for (; vars; vars = TREE_CHAIN (vars))
4287 {
4288 tree var = TREE_VALUE (vars);
4289 tree init = TREE_PURPOSE (vars);
4290 one_static_initialization_or_destruction (var, init, true);
4291
4292#ifdef ASM_OUTPUT_DEF
4293 /* Output init aliases even with -fno-extern-tls-init. */
4294 if (TREE_PUBLIC (var))
4295 {
4296 tree single_init_fn = get_tls_init_fn (var);
4297 if (single_init_fn == NULL_TREE)
4298 continue;
4299 cgraph_node *alias
4300 = cgraph_node::get_create (fn)->create_same_body_alias
4301 (single_init_fn, fn);
4302 gcc_assert (alias != NULL);
4303 }
4304#endif
4305 }
4306
4307 finish_then_clause (if_stmt);
4308 finish_if_stmt (if_stmt);
4309 finish_function_body (body);
4310 expand_or_defer_fn (finish_function (0));
4311}
4312
4313/* We're at the end of compilation, so generate any mangling aliases that
4314 we've been saving up, if DECL is going to be output and ID2 isn't
4315 already taken by another declaration. */
4316
4317static void
4318generate_mangling_alias (tree decl, tree id2)
4319{
4320 /* If there's a declaration already using this mangled name,
4321 don't create a compatibility alias that conflicts. */
4322 if (IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (id2))
4323 return;
4324
4325 struct cgraph_node *n = NULL;
4326 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
4327 && !(n = cgraph_node::get (decl)))
4328 /* Don't create an alias to an unreferenced function. */
4329 return;
4330
4331 tree alias = make_alias_for (decl, id2);
4332 SET_IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (id2, alias);
4333 DECL_IGNORED_P (alias) = 1;
4334 TREE_PUBLIC (alias) = TREE_PUBLIC (decl);
4335 DECL_VISIBILITY (alias) = DECL_VISIBILITY (decl);
4336 if (vague_linkage_p (decl))
4337 DECL_WEAK (alias) = 1;
4338 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
4339 n->create_same_body_alias (alias, decl);
4340 else
4341 varpool_node::create_extra_name_alias (alias, decl);
4342}
4343
4344/* Note that we might want to emit an alias with the symbol ID2 for DECL at
4345 the end of translation, for compatibility across bugs in the mangling
4346 implementation. */
4347
4348void
4349note_mangling_alias (tree decl ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED, tree id2 ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
4350{
4351#ifdef ASM_OUTPUT_DEF
4352 if (!defer_mangling_aliases)
4353 generate_mangling_alias (decl, id2);
4354 else
4355 {
4356 vec_safe_push (mangling_aliases, decl);
4357 vec_safe_push (mangling_aliases, id2);
4358 }
4359#endif
4360}
4361
4362/* Emit all mangling aliases that were deferred up to this point. */
4363
4364void
4365generate_mangling_aliases ()
4366{
4367 while (!vec_safe_is_empty (mangling_aliases))
4368 {
4369 tree id2 = mangling_aliases->pop();
4370 tree decl = mangling_aliases->pop();
4371 generate_mangling_alias (decl, id2);
4372 }
4373 defer_mangling_aliases = false;
4374}

4392static location_t locus_at_end_of_parsing;

4394/* Check the deallocation functions for CODE to see if we want to warn that
4395 only one was defined. */
4396
4397static void
4398maybe_warn_sized_delete (enum tree_code code)
4399{
4400 tree sized = NULL_TREE;
4401 tree unsized = NULL_TREE;
4402
4403 for (tree ovl = IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (cp_operator_id (code));
4404 ovl; ovl = OVL_NEXT (ovl))
4405 {
4406 tree fn = OVL_CURRENT (ovl);
4407 /* We're only interested in usual deallocation functions. */
4408 if (!usual_deallocation_fn_p (fn))
4409 continue;
4410 if (FUNCTION_ARG_CHAIN (fn) == void_list_node)
4411 unsized = fn;
4412 else
4413 sized = fn;
4414 }
4415 if (DECL_INITIAL (unsized) && !DECL_INITIAL (sized))
4416 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (unsized), OPT_Wsized_deallocation,
4417 "the program should also define %qD", sized);
4418 else if (!DECL_INITIAL (unsized) && DECL_INITIAL (sized))
4419 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (sized), OPT_Wsized_deallocation,
4420 "the program should also define %qD", unsized);
4421}

4423/* Check the global deallocation functions to see if we want to warn about
4424 defining unsized without sized (or vice versa). */
4425
4426static void
4427maybe_warn_sized_delete ()
4428{
4429 if (!flag_sized_deallocation || !warn_sized_deallocation)
4430 return;
4431 maybe_warn_sized_delete (DELETE_EXPR);
4432 maybe_warn_sized_delete (VEC_DELETE_EXPR);
4433}

4435/* Earlier we left PTRMEM_CST in variable initializers alone so that we could
4436 look them up when evaluating non-type template parameters. Now we need to
4437 lower them to something the back end can understand. */
4438
4439static void
4440lower_var_init ()
4441{
4442 varpool_node *node;
4443 FOR_EACH_VARIABLE (node)
4444 {
4445 tree d = node->decl;
4446 if (tree init = DECL_INITIAL (d))
4447 DECL_INITIAL (d) = cplus_expand_constant (init);
4448 }
4449}
4450
4451/* This routine is called at the end of compilation.
4452 Its job is to create all the code needed to initialize and
4453 destroy the global aggregates. We do the destruction
4454 first, since that way we only need to reverse the decls once. */
4455
4456void
4457c_parse_final_cleanups (void)
4458{
4459 tree vars;
4460 bool reconsider;
4461 size_t i;
4462 unsigned ssdf_count = 0;
4463 int retries = 0;
4464 tree decl;
4465
4466 locus_at_end_of_parsing = input_location;
4467 at_eof = 1;
4468
4469 /* Bad parse errors. Just forget about it. */
4470 if (! global_bindings_p () || current_class_type
4471 || !vec_safe_is_empty (decl_namespace_list))
4472 return;
4473
4474 /* This is the point to write out a PCH if we're doing that.
4475 In that case we do not want to do anything else. */
4476 if (pch_file)
4477 {
4478 /* Mangle all symbols at PCH creation time. */
4479 symtab_node *node;
4480 FOR_EACH_SYMBOL (node)
4481 if (! is_a <varpool_node *> (node)
4482 || ! DECL_HARD_REGISTER (node->decl))
4483 DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (node->decl);
4484 c_common_write_pch ();
4485 dump_tu ();
4486 /* Ensure even the callers don't try to finalize the CU. */
4487 flag_syntax_only = 1;
4488 return;
4489 }
4490
4491 timevar_stop (TV_PHASE_PARSING);
4492 timevar_start (TV_PHASE_DEFERRED);
4493
4494 symtab->process_same_body_aliases ();
4495
4496 /* Handle -fdump-ada-spec[-slim] */
4497 if (flag_dump_ada_spec || flag_dump_ada_spec_slim)
4498 {
4499 if (flag_dump_ada_spec_slim)
4500 collect_source_ref (main_input_filename);
4501 else
4502 collect_source_refs (global_namespace);
4503
4504 dump_ada_specs (collect_all_refs, cpp_check);
4505 }
4506
4507 /* FIXME - huh? was input_line -= 1;*/
4508
4509 /* We now have to write out all the stuff we put off writing out.
4510 These include:
4511
4512 o Template specializations that we have not yet instantiated,
4513 but which are needed.
4514 o Initialization and destruction for non-local objects with
4515 static storage duration. (Local objects with static storage
4516 duration are initialized when their scope is first entered,
4517 and are cleaned up via atexit.)
4518 o Virtual function tables.
4519
4520 All of these may cause others to be needed. For example,
4521 instantiating one function may cause another to be needed, and
4522 generating the initializer for an object may cause templates to be
4523 instantiated, etc., etc. */
4524
4525 emit_support_tinfos ();
4526
4527 do
4528 {
4529 tree t;
4530 tree decl;
4531
4532 reconsider = false;
4533
4534 /* If there are templates that we've put off instantiating, do
4535 them now. */
4536 instantiate_pending_templates (retries);
4537 ggc_collect ();
4538
4539 /* Write out virtual tables as required. Note that writing out
4540 the virtual table for a template class may cause the
4541 instantiation of members of that class. If we write out
4542 vtables then we remove the class from our list so we don't
4543 have to look at it again. */
4544
4545 while (keyed_classes != NULL_TREE
4546 && maybe_emit_vtables (TREE_VALUE (keyed_classes)))
4547 {
4548 reconsider = true;
4549 keyed_classes = TREE_CHAIN (keyed_classes);
4550 }
4551
4552 t = keyed_classes;
4553 if (t != NULL_TREE)
4554 {
4555 tree next = TREE_CHAIN (t);
4556
4557 while (next)
4558 {
4559 if (maybe_emit_vtables (TREE_VALUE (next)))
4560 {
4561 reconsider = true;
4562 TREE_CHAIN (t) = TREE_CHAIN (next);
4563 }
4564 else
4565 t = next;
4566
4567 next = TREE_CHAIN (t);
4568 }
4569 }
4570
4571 /* Write out needed type info variables. We have to be careful
4572 looping through unemitted decls, because emit_tinfo_decl may
4573 cause other variables to be needed. New elements will be
4574 appended, and we remove from the vector those that actually
4575 get emitted. */
4576 for (i = unemitted_tinfo_decls->length ();
4577 unemitted_tinfo_decls->iterate (--i, &t);)
4578 if (emit_tinfo_decl (t))
4579 {
4580 reconsider = true;
4581 unemitted_tinfo_decls->unordered_remove (i);
4582 }
4583
4584 /* The list of objects with static storage duration is built up
4585 in reverse order. We clear STATIC_AGGREGATES so that any new
4586 aggregates added during the initialization of these will be
4587 initialized in the correct order when we next come around the
4588 loop. */
4589 vars = prune_vars_needing_no_initialization (&static_aggregates);
4590
4591 if (vars)
4592 {
4593 /* We need to start a new initialization function each time
4594 through the loop. That's because we need to know which
4595 vtables have been referenced, and TREE_SYMBOL_REFERENCED
4596 isn't computed until a function is finished, and written
4597 out. That's a deficiency in the back end. When this is
4598 fixed, these initialization functions could all become
4599 inline, with resulting performance improvements. */
4600 tree ssdf_body;
4601
4602 /* Set the line and file, so that it is obviously not from
4603 the source file. */
4604 input_location = locus_at_end_of_parsing;
4605 ssdf_body = start_static_storage_duration_function (ssdf_count);
4606
4607 /* Make sure the back end knows about all the variables. */
4608 write_out_vars (vars);
4609
4610 /* First generate code to do all the initializations. */
4611 if (vars)
4612 do_static_initialization_or_destruction (vars, /*initp=*/true);
4613
4614 /* Then, generate code to do all the destructions. Do these
4615 in reverse order so that the most recently constructed
4616 variable is the first destroyed. If we're using
4617 __cxa_atexit, then we don't need to do this; functions
4618 were registered at initialization time to destroy the
4619 local statics. */
4620 if (!flag_use_cxa_atexit && vars)
4621 {
4622 vars = nreverse (vars);
4623 do_static_initialization_or_destruction (vars, /*initp=*/false);
4624 }
4625 else
4626 vars = NULL_TREE;
4627
4628 /* Finish up the static storage duration function for this
4629 round. */
4630 input_location = locus_at_end_of_parsing;
4631 finish_static_storage_duration_function (ssdf_body);
4632
4633 /* All those initializations and finalizations might cause
4634 us to need more inline functions, more template
4635 instantiations, etc. */
4636 reconsider = true;
4637 ssdf_count++;
4638 /* ??? was: locus_at_end_of_parsing.line++; */
4639 }
4640
4641 /* Now do the same for thread_local variables. */
4642 handle_tls_init ();
4643
4644 /* Go through the set of inline functions whose bodies have not
4645 been emitted yet. If out-of-line copies of these functions
4646 are required, emit them. */
4647 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (deferred_fns, i, decl)
4648 {
4649 /* Does it need synthesizing? */
4650 if (DECL_DEFAULTED_FN (decl) && ! DECL_INITIAL (decl)
4651 && (! DECL_REALLY_EXTERN (decl) || possibly_inlined_p (decl)))
4652 {
4653 /* Even though we're already at the top-level, we push
4654 there again. That way, when we pop back a few lines
4655 hence, all of our state is restored. Otherwise,
4656 finish_function doesn't clean things up, and we end
4657 up with CURRENT_FUNCTION_DECL set. */
4658 push_to_top_level ();
4659 /* The decl's location will mark where it was first
4660 needed. Save that so synthesize method can indicate
4661 where it was needed from, in case of error */
4662 input_location = DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl);
4663 synthesize_method (decl);
4664 pop_from_top_level ();
4665 reconsider = true;
4666 }
4667
4668 if (!DECL_INITIAL (decl) && decl_tls_wrapper_p (decl))
4669 generate_tls_wrapper (decl);
4670
4671 if (!DECL_SAVED_TREE (decl))
4672 continue;
4673
4674 cgraph_node *node = cgraph_node::get_create (decl);
4675
4676 /* We lie to the back end, pretending that some functions
4677 are not defined when they really are. This keeps these
4678 functions from being put out unnecessarily. But, we must
4679 stop lying when the functions are referenced, or if they
4680 are not comdat since they need to be put out now. If
4681 DECL_INTERFACE_KNOWN, then we have already set
4682 DECL_EXTERNAL appropriately, so there's no need to check
4683 again, and we do not want to clear DECL_EXTERNAL if a
4684 previous call to import_export_decl set it.
4685
4686 This is done in a separate for cycle, because if some
4687 deferred function is contained in another deferred
4688 function later in deferred_fns varray,
4689 rest_of_compilation would skip this function and we
4690 really cannot expand the same function twice. */
4691 import_export_decl (decl);
4692 if (DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (decl)
4693 && DECL_INITIAL (decl)
4694 && decl_needed_p (decl))
4695 {
4696 if (node->cpp_implicit_alias)
4697 node = node->get_alias_target ();
4698
4699 node->call_for_symbol_thunks_and_aliases (clear_decl_external,
4700 NULL, true);
4701 /* If we mark !DECL_EXTERNAL one of the symbols in some comdat
4702 group, we need to mark all symbols in the same comdat group
4703 that way. */
4704 if (node->same_comdat_group)
4705 for (cgraph_node *next
4706 = dyn_cast<cgraph_node *> (node->same_comdat_group);
4707 next != node;
4708 next = dyn_cast<cgraph_node *> (next->same_comdat_group))
4709 next->call_for_symbol_thunks_and_aliases (clear_decl_external,
4710 NULL, true);
4711 }
4712
4713 /* If we're going to need to write this function out, and
4714 there's already a body for it, create RTL for it now.
4715 (There might be no body if this is a method we haven't
4716 gotten around to synthesizing yet.) */
4717 if (!DECL_EXTERNAL (decl)
4718 && decl_needed_p (decl)
4719 && !TREE_ASM_WRITTEN (decl)
4720 && !node->definition)
4721 {
4722 /* We will output the function; no longer consider it in this
4723 loop. */
4724 DECL_DEFER_OUTPUT (decl) = 0;
4725 /* Generate RTL for this function now that we know we
4726 need it. */
4727 expand_or_defer_fn (decl);
4728 /* If we're compiling -fsyntax-only pretend that this
4729 function has been written out so that we don't try to
4730 expand it again. */
4731 if (flag_syntax_only)
4732 TREE_ASM_WRITTEN (decl) = 1;
4733 reconsider = true;
4734 }
4735 }
4736
4737 if (walk_namespaces (wrapup_globals_for_namespace, /*data=*/0))
4738 reconsider = true;
4739
4740 /* Static data members are just like namespace-scope globals. */
4741 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (pending_statics, i, decl)
4742 {
4743 if (var_finalized_p (decl) || DECL_REALLY_EXTERN (decl)
4744 /* Don't write it out if we haven't seen a definition. */
4745 || (DECL_IN_AGGR_P (decl) && !DECL_INLINE_VAR_P (decl)))
4746 continue;
4747 import_export_decl (decl);
4748 /* If this static data member is needed, provide it to the
4749 back end. */
4750 if (DECL_NOT_REALLY_EXTERN (decl) && decl_needed_p (decl))
4751 DECL_EXTERNAL (decl) = 0;
4752 }
4753 if (vec_safe_length (pending_statics) != 0
4754 && wrapup_global_declarations (pending_statics->address (),
4755 pending_statics->length ()))
4756 reconsider = true;
4757
4758 retries++;
4759 }
4760 while (reconsider);
4761
4762 walk_namespaces (diagnose_inline_vars_for_namespace, /*data=*/0);
4763
4764 lower_var_init ();
4765
4766 generate_mangling_aliases ();
4767
4768 /* All used inline functions must have a definition at this point. */
4769 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (deferred_fns, i, decl)
4770 {
4771 if (/* Check online inline functions that were actually used. */
4772 DECL_ODR_USED (decl) && DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl)
4773 /* If the definition actually was available here, then the
4774 fact that the function was not defined merely represents
4775 that for some reason (use of a template repository,
4776 #pragma interface, etc.) we decided not to emit the
4777 definition here. */
4778 && !DECL_INITIAL (decl)
4779 /* Don't complain if the template was defined. */
4780 && !(DECL_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATION (decl)
4781 && DECL_INITIAL (DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT
4782 (template_for_substitution (decl)))))
4783 {
4784 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), 0,
4785 "inline function %qD used but never defined", decl);
4786 /* Avoid a duplicate warning from check_global_declaration. */
4787 TREE_NO_WARNING (decl) = 1;
4788 }
4789 }
4790
4791 /* So must decls that use a type with no linkage. */
4792 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (no_linkage_decls, i, decl)
4793 no_linkage_error (decl);
4794
4795 maybe_warn_sized_delete ();
4796
4797 /* Then, do the Objective-C stuff. This is where all the
4798 Objective-C module stuff gets generated (symtab,
4799 class/protocol/selector lists etc). This must be done after C++
4800 templates, destructors etc. so that selectors used in C++
4801 templates are properly allocated. */
4802 if (c_dialect_objc ())
4803 objc_write_global_declarations ();
4804
4805 /* We give C linkage to static constructors and destructors. */
4806 push_lang_context (lang_name_c);
4807
4808 /* Generate initialization and destruction functions for all
4809 priorities for which they are required. */
4810 if (priority_info_map)
4811 splay_tree_foreach (priority_info_map,
4812 generate_ctor_and_dtor_functions_for_priority,
4813 /*data=*/&locus_at_end_of_parsing);
4814 else if (c_dialect_objc () && objc_static_init_needed_p ())
4815 /* If this is obj-c++ and we need a static init, call
4816 generate_ctor_or_dtor_function. */
4817 generate_ctor_or_dtor_function (/*constructor_p=*/true,
4818 DEFAULT_INIT_PRIORITY,
4819 &locus_at_end_of_parsing);
4820
4821 /* We're done with the splay-tree now. */
4822 if (priority_info_map)
4823 splay_tree_delete (priority_info_map);
4824
4825 /* Generate any missing aliases. */
4826 maybe_apply_pending_pragma_weaks ();
4827
4828 /* We're done with static constructors, so we can go back to "C++"
4829 linkage now. */
4830 pop_lang_context ();
4831
4832 if (flag_vtable_verify)
4833 {
4834 vtv_recover_class_info ();
4835 vtv_compute_class_hierarchy_transitive_closure ();
4836 vtv_build_vtable_verify_fndecl ();
4837 }
4838
4839 perform_deferred_noexcept_checks ();
4840
4841 finish_repo ();
4842
4843 fini_constexpr ();
4844
4845 /* The entire file is now complete. If requested, dump everything
4846 to a file. */
4847 dump_tu ();
4848
4849 if (flag_detailed_statistics)
4850 {
4851 dump_tree_statistics ();
4852 dump_time_statistics ();
4853 }
4854
4855 timevar_stop (TV_PHASE_DEFERRED);
4856 timevar_start (TV_PHASE_PARSING);
4857
4858 /* Indicate that we're done with front end processing. */
4859 at_eof = 2;
4860}

4863 This should really go away. No front-end should need to do
4864 anything past the compilation process. */
4865
4866void
4867cxx_post_compilation_parsing_cleanups (void)
4868{

4870
4871 if (flag_vtable_verify)
4872 {
4873 /* Generate the special constructor initialization function that
4874 calls __VLTRegisterPairs, and give it a very high
4875 initialization priority. This must be done after
4876 finalize_compilation_unit so that we have accurate
4877 information about which vtable will actually be emitted. */
4878 vtv_generate_init_routine ();
4879 }
4880
4881 input_location = locus_at_end_of_parsing;

4884 validate_conversion_obstack ();
4885
4886 timevar_stop (TV_PHASE_LATE_PARSING_CLEANUPS);

4889/* FN is an OFFSET_REF, DOTSTAR_EXPR or MEMBER_REF indicating the
4890 function to call in parse-tree form; it has not yet been
4891 semantically analyzed. ARGS are the arguments to the function.
4892 They have already been semantically analyzed. This may change
4893 ARGS. */
4894
4895tree
4896build_offset_ref_call_from_tree (tree fn, vec<tree, va_gc> **args,
4897 tsubst_flags_t complain)
4898{
4899 tree orig_fn;
4900 vec<tree, va_gc> *orig_args = NULL;
4901 tree expr;
4902 tree object;
4903
4904 orig_fn = fn;
4905 object = TREE_OPERAND (fn, 0);
4906
4907 if (processing_template_decl)
4908 {
4909 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (fn) == DOTSTAR_EXPR
4910 || TREE_CODE (fn) == MEMBER_REF);
4911 if (type_dependent_expression_p (fn)
4912 || any_type_dependent_arguments_p (*args))
4913 return build_nt_call_vec (fn, *args);
4914
4915 orig_args = make_tree_vector_copy (*args);
4916
4917 /* Transform the arguments and add the implicit "this"
4918 parameter. That must be done before the FN is transformed
4919 because we depend on the form of FN. */
4920 make_args_non_dependent (*args);
4921 object = build_non_dependent_expr (object);
4922 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (fn)) == METHOD_TYPE)
4923 {
4924 if (TREE_CODE (fn) == DOTSTAR_EXPR)
4925 object = cp_build_addr_expr (object, complain);
4926 vec_safe_insert (*args, 0, object);
4927 }
4928 /* Now that the arguments are done, transform FN. */
4929 fn = build_non_dependent_expr (fn);
4930 }
4931
4932 /* A qualified name corresponding to a bound pointer-to-member is
4933 represented as an OFFSET_REF:
4934
4935 struct B { void g(); };
4936 void (B::*p)();
4937 void B::g() { (this->*p)(); } */
4938 if (TREE_CODE (fn) == OFFSET_REF)
4939 {
4940 tree object_addr = cp_build_addr_expr (object, complain);
4941 fn = TREE_OPERAND (fn, 1);
4942 fn = get_member_function_from_ptrfunc (&object_addr, fn,
4943 complain);
4944 vec_safe_insert (*args, 0, object_addr);
4945 }
4946
4947 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (fn)))
4948 expr = build_op_call (fn, args, complain);
4949 else
4950 expr = cp_build_function_call_vec (fn, args, complain);
4951 if (processing_template_decl && expr != error_mark_node)
4952 expr = build_min_non_dep_call_vec (expr, orig_fn, orig_args);
4953
4954 if (orig_args != NULL)
4955 release_tree_vector (orig_args);
4956
4957 return expr;
4958}

4961void
4962check_default_args (tree x)
4963{
4964 tree arg = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (x));
4965 bool saw_def = false;
4966 int i = 0 - (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (x)) == METHOD_TYPE);
4967 for (; arg && arg != void_list_node; arg = TREE_CHAIN (arg), ++i)
4968 {
4969 if (TREE_PURPOSE (arg))
4970 saw_def = true;
4971 else if (saw_def && !PACK_EXPANSION_P (TREE_VALUE (arg)))
4972 {
4973 error ("default argument missing for parameter %P of %q+#D", i, x);
4974 TREE_PURPOSE (arg) = error_mark_node;
4975 }
4976 }
4977}
