4979/* Return true if function DECL can be inlined. This is used to force
4980 instantiation of methods that might be interesting for inlining. */
4981bool
4982possibly_inlined_p (tree decl)
4983{
4984 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL);
4985 if (DECL_UNINLINABLE (decl))
4986 return false;
4987 if (!optimize)
4988 return DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl);
4989 /* When optimizing, we might inline everything when flatten
4990 attribute or heuristics inlining for size or autoinlining
4991 is used. */
4992 return true;
4993}
4994
4995/* Normally, we can wait until instantiation-time to synthesize DECL.
4996 However, if DECL is a static data member initialized with a constant
4997 or a constexpr function, we need it right now because a reference to
4998 such a data member or a call to such function is not value-dependent.
4999 For a function that uses auto in the return type, we need to instantiate
5000 it to find out its type. For OpenMP user defined reductions, we need
5001 them instantiated for reduction clauses which inline them by hand
5002 directly. */
5003
5004static void
5005maybe_instantiate_decl (tree decl)
5006{
5007 if (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl)
5008 && DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (decl)
5009 && (decl_maybe_constant_var_p (decl)
5010 || (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
5011 && DECL_OMP_DECLARE_REDUCTION_P (decl))
5012 || undeduced_auto_decl (decl))
5013 && !DECL_DECLARED_CONCEPT_P (decl)
5014 && !uses_template_parms (DECL_TI_ARGS (decl)))
5015 {
5016 /* Instantiating a function will result in garbage collection. We
5017 must treat this situation as if we were within the body of a
5018 function so as to avoid collecting live data only referenced from
5019 the stack (such as overload resolution candidates). */
5020 ++function_depth;
5021 instantiate_decl (decl, /*defer_ok=*/false,
5022 /*expl_inst_class_mem_p=*/false);
5023 --function_depth;
5024 }
5025}
5026
5027/* Mark DECL (either a _DECL or a BASELINK) as "used" in the program.
5028 If DECL is a specialization or implicitly declared class member,
5029 generate the actual definition. Return false if something goes
5030 wrong, true otherwise. */
5031
5032bool
5033mark_used (tree decl, tsubst_flags_t complain)
5034{
5035 /* If DECL is a BASELINK for a single function, then treat it just
5036 like the DECL for the function. Otherwise, if the BASELINK is
5037 for an overloaded function, we don't know which function was
5038 actually used until after overload resolution. */
5039 if (BASELINK_P (decl))
5040 {
5041 decl = BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (decl);
5042 if (really_overloaded_fn (decl))
5043 return true;
5044 decl = OVL_CURRENT (decl);
5045 }
5046
5047 /* Set TREE_USED for the benefit of -Wunused. */
5048 TREE_USED (decl) = 1;
5049
5050 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TEMPLATE_DECL)
5051 return true;
5052
5053 if (DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (decl))
5054 TREE_USED (DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION (decl)) = 1;
5055
5056 /* Mark enumeration types as used. */
5057 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == CONST_DECL)
5058 used_types_insert (DECL_CONTEXT (decl));
5059
5060 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
5061 maybe_instantiate_noexcept (decl);
5062
5063 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
5064 && DECL_DELETED_FN (decl))
5065 {
5066 if (DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl))
5067 {
5068 if (DECL_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_P (decl) == TYPE_EXPR
5069 && LAMBDA_TYPE_P (DECL_CONTEXT (decl)))
5070 {
5071 /* We mark a lambda conversion op as deleted if we can't
5072 generate it properly; see maybe_add_lambda_conv_op. */
5073 sorry ("converting lambda which uses %<...%> to "
5074 "function pointer");
5075 return false;
5076 }
5077 }
5078 if (complain & tf_error)
5079 {
5080 error ("use of deleted function %qD", decl);
5081 if (!maybe_explain_implicit_delete (decl))
5082 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), "declared here");
5083 }
5084 return false;
5085 }
5086
5087 if (TREE_DEPRECATED (decl) && (complain & tf_warning)
5088 && deprecated_state != DEPRECATED_SUPPRESS)
5089 warn_deprecated_use (decl, NULL_TREE);
5090
5091 /* We can only check DECL_ODR_USED on variables or functions with
5092 DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC set, and these are also the only decls that we
5093 might need special handling for. */
5094 if (!VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (decl)
5095 || DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl) == NULL
5096 || DECL_THUNK_P (decl))
5097 {
5098 if (!processing_template_decl
5099 && !require_deduced_type (decl, complain))
5100 return false;
5101 return true;
5102 }
5103
5104 /* We only want to do this processing once. We don't need to keep trying
5105 to instantiate inline templates, because unit-at-a-time will make sure
5106 we get them compiled before functions that want to inline them. */
5107 if (DECL_ODR_USED (decl))
5108 return true;
5109
5110 /* Normally, we can wait until instantiation-time to synthesize DECL.
5111 However, if DECL is a static data member initialized with a constant
5112 or a constexpr function, we need it right now because a reference to
5113 such a data member or a call to such function is not value-dependent.
5114 For a function that uses auto in the return type, we need to instantiate
5115 it to find out its type. For OpenMP user defined reductions, we need
5116 them instantiated for reduction clauses which inline them by hand
5117 directly. */
5118 maybe_instantiate_decl (decl);
5119
5120 if (processing_template_decl || in_template_function ())
5121 return true;
5122
5123 /* Check this too in case we're within instantiate_non_dependent_expr. */
5124 if (DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (decl)
5125 && uses_template_parms (DECL_TI_ARGS (decl)))
5126 return true;
5127
5128 if (!require_deduced_type (decl, complain))
5129 return false;
5130
5131 /* If we don't need a value, then we don't need to synthesize DECL. */
5132 if (cp_unevaluated_operand || in_discarded_stmt)
5133 return true;
5134
5135 DECL_ODR_USED (decl) = 1;
5136 if (DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (decl))
5137 DECL_ODR_USED (DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION (decl)) = 1;
5138
5139 /* DR 757: A type without linkage shall not be used as the type of a
5140 variable or function with linkage, unless
5141 o the variable or function has extern "C" linkage (7.5 [dcl.link]), or
5142 o the variable or function is not used (3.2 [basic.def.odr]) or is
5143 defined in the same translation unit. */
5144 if (cxx_dialect > cxx98
5145 && decl_linkage (decl) != lk_none
5146 && !DECL_EXTERN_C_P (decl)
5147 && !DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl)
5148 && !decl_defined_p (decl)
5149 && no_linkage_check (TREE_TYPE (decl), /*relaxed_p=*/false))
5150 {
5151 if (is_local_extern (decl))
5152 /* There's no way to define a local extern, and adding it to
5153 the vector interferes with GC, so give an error now. */
5154 no_linkage_error (decl);
5155 else
5156 vec_safe_push (no_linkage_decls, decl);
5157 }
5158
5159 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL && DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl)
5160 && !DECL_INITIAL (decl) && !DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl))
5161 /* Remember it, so we can check it was defined. */
5162 note_vague_linkage_fn (decl);
5163
5164 /* Is it a synthesized method that needs to be synthesized? */
5165 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
5166 && DECL_NONSTATIC_MEMBER_FUNCTION_P (decl)
5167 && DECL_DEFAULTED_FN (decl)
5168 /* A function defaulted outside the class is synthesized either by
5169 cp_finish_decl or instantiate_decl. */
5170 && !DECL_DEFAULTED_OUTSIDE_CLASS_P (decl)
5171 && ! DECL_INITIAL (decl))
5172 {
5173 /* Defer virtual destructors so that thunks get the right
5174 linkage. */
5175 if (DECL_VIRTUAL_P (decl) && !at_eof)
5176 {
5177 note_vague_linkage_fn (decl);
5178 return true;
5179 }
5180
5181 /* Remember the current location for a function we will end up
5182 synthesizing. Then we can inform the user where it was
5183 required in the case of error. */
5184 DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl) = input_location;
5185
5186 /* Synthesizing an implicitly defined member function will result in
5187 garbage collection. We must treat this situation as if we were
5188 within the body of a function so as to avoid collecting live data
5189 on the stack (such as overload resolution candidates).
5190
5191 We could just let cp_write_global_declarations handle synthesizing
5192 this function by adding it to deferred_fns, but doing
5193 it at the use site produces better error messages. */
5194 ++function_depth;
5195 synthesize_method (decl);
5196 --function_depth;
5197 /* If this is a synthesized method we don't need to
5198 do the instantiation test below. */
5199 }
5200 else if (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (decl)
5201 && DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (decl)
5202 && !DECL_DECLARED_CONCEPT_P (decl)
5203 && (!DECL_EXPLICIT_INSTANTIATION (decl)
5204 || always_instantiate_p (decl)))
5205 /* If this is a function or variable that is an instance of some
5206 template, we now know that we will need to actually do the
5207 instantiation. We check that DECL is not an explicit
5208 instantiation because that is not checked in instantiate_decl.
5209
5210 We put off instantiating functions in order to improve compile
5211 times. Maintaining a stack of active functions is expensive,
5212 and the inliner knows to instantiate any functions it might
5213 need. Therefore, we always try to defer instantiation. */
5214 {
5215 ++function_depth;
5216 instantiate_decl (decl, /*defer_ok=*/true,
5217 /*expl_inst_class_mem_p=*/false);
5218 --function_depth;
5219 }
5220
5221 return true;
5222}

5224bool
5225mark_used (tree decl)
5226{
5227 return mark_used (decl, tf_warning_or_error);
5228}

5237vtv_finish_verification_constructor_init_function (tree function_body)
5238{

5240
5241 finish_compound_stmt (function_body);
